{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877934888,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a92b651001WYMaV0S1GtAuml","messageID":"msg_d7a9290250017FrAY3CuGOfCM4","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:3","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-016 Design: PicoD File Management API\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-016  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** M (Medium)\n9: \n10: The PicoD File Management API provides a unified interface for file operations within sandboxed environments. It supports file upload/download, directory listing, file operations (create, delete, move, copy), path security enforcement, and quota management.\n11: \n12: This implementation integrates with:\n13: - **Sandbox Interface (AR-009)**: For actual file operations in sandbox environments\n14: - **Status Store (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)**: For operation tracking and quota persistence\n15: - **PicoD Command Execution (AR-015)**: For complementary command-based file operations\n16: \n17: ---\n18: \n19: ## Architecture\n20: \n21: ### High-Level Design\n22: \n23: ```\n24: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n25: │                         Client Applications                                  │\n26: │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                         │\n27: │  │  Workload   │  │   CLI       │  │  Session    │                         │\n28: │  │  Manager    │  │   Toolkit   │  │  Manager    │                         │\n29: │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                         │\n30: └─────────┼────────────────┼────────────────┼────────────────────────────────┘\n31:           │                │                │\n32:           ▼                ▼                ▼\n33: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n34: │                      PicoD FileManager API                                   │\n35: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐ │\n36: │  │                      FileManager Interface                              │ │\n37: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐ │ │\n38: │  │  │   Upload()      │  │   Download()    │  │   List()               │ │ │\n39: │  │  │   · Single      │  │   · Stream      │  │   · Filter             │ │ │\n40: │  │  │   · Chunked     │  │   · Archive     │  │   · Paginate           │ │ │\n41: │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────────┘ │ │\n42: │  │  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌─────────────────┐  ┌────────────────────────┐ │ │\n43: │  │  │   Delete()      │  │   Move()        │  │   Copy()               │ │ │\n44: │  │  │   Mkdir()       │  │   Rmdir()       │  │   GetMetadata()        │ │ │\n45: │  │  └─────────────────┘  └─────────────────┘  └────────────────────────┘ │ │\n46: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘ │\n47: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n48: │                      File Operations Layer                                   │\n49: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n50: │  │  PathValidator   │  │  UploadManager   │  │  DownloadManager         │  │\n51: │  │  · Security      │  │  · Chunking      │  │  · Streaming             │  │\n52: │  │  · Normalization │  │  · Checksums     │  │  · Archiving             │  │\n53: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n54: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n55: │  │  QuotaManager    │  │  FileWatcher     │  │  TransferBuffer          │  │\n56: │  │  · Tracking      │  │  · Events        │  │  · Circular              │  │\n57: │  │  · Enforcement   │  │  · Notifications │  │  · Streaming             │  │\n58: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n59: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n60: │                      Sandbox Interface (AR-009)                              │\n61: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐  │\n62: │  │  Sandbox Resolver│  │  File Operations │  │  Workspace Access        │  │\n63: │  │  · Session lookup│  │  · Read/Write    │  │  · Isolation             │  │\n64: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘  │\n65: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n66: │                      Status Store (AR-012/13/14)                             │\n67: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐                                │\n68: │  │  Redis/Valkey    │  │  QuotaStore      │                                │\n69: │  │  · Upload state  │  │  · Usage cache   │                                │\n70: │  │  · TTL support   │  │  · Limits        │                                │\n71: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘                                │\n72: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n73: ```\n74: \n75: ### Component Architecture\n76: \n77: ```\n78: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n79: │                           File Upload Flow                                   │\n80: │                                                                              │\n81: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n82: │  │  Client  │──▶│  Upload  │──▶│ Validate │──▶│   Check  │──▶│  Resolve │  │\n83: │  │  Request │   │  Method  │   │  Request │   │   Quota  │   │   Path   │  │\n84: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n85: │                                                    │                │        │\n86: │                         ┌──────────────────────────┘                │        │\n87: │                         ▼                                           │        │\n88: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────┴─────┐  │\n89: │  │  Return  │◀──│  Update  │◀──│  Verify  │◀──│ Transfer │◀──│   Check    │  │\n90: │  │  Result  │   │  Quota   │   │ Checksum │   │   File   │   │  Sandbox   │  │\n91: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────────────┘  │\n92: │                                                                              │\n93: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n94: ```\n95: \n96: ### Component Interactions\n97: \n98: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n99: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n100: | **FileManager** | Primary API for file operations | `UploadRequest`, `DownloadRequest`, `ListRequest`, etc. | `UploadResult`, `DownloadResult`, `ListResult`, error |\n101: | **PathValidator** | Validates and secures file paths | Raw path string | Validated, absolute path or error |\n102: | **UploadManager** | Handles upload operations with chunking | `UploadRequest`, `UploadChunkRequest` | `UploadResult`, `UploadChunkResult` |\n103: | **DownloadManager** | Handles download with streaming | `DownloadRequest` | `DownloadResult` with `io.ReadCloser` |\n104: | **QuotaManager** | Tracks and enforces storage quotas | Session ID, operation type, size | Quota status, allowance or error |\n105: | **FileWatcher** | Provides file change notifications | `WatchRequest` | File event channel |\n106: | **SandboxResolver** | Resolves session IDs to sandbox | `SessionID` | `SandboxInfo` |\n107: | **TransferBuffer** | Buffers transfer data | Data chunks | Buffered data for streaming |\n108: \n109: ---\n110: \n111: ## Directory Structure\n112: \n113: ```\n114: pkg/picod/\n115: ├── file_manager.go          # FileManager interface and implementation (~300 lines)\n116: ├── file_types.go            # File operation type definitions (~120 lines)\n117: ├── upload.go                # Upload handling and chunking (~150 lines)\n118: ├── download.go              # Download handling and streaming (~150 lines)\n119: ├── path.go                  # Path validation and security (~100 lines)\n120: ├── quota.go                 # Quota management and tracking (~80 lines)\n121: ├── file_errors.go           # File-specific error definitions (~60 lines)\n122: └── file_manager_test.go     # Unit tests (~250 lines)\n123: ```\n124: \n125: ---\n126: \n127: ## Data Structures\n128: \n129: ### Request DTOs\n130: \n131: #### UploadRequest / UploadResult\n132: \n133: ```go\n134: // UploadRequest contains parameters for file upload.\n135: type UploadRequest struct {\n136: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n137: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n138: \n139: \t// SourcePath is the path on the host (required)\n140: \tSourcePath string `json:\"sourcePath\" validate:\"required\"`\n141: \n142: \t// DestinationPath is the path in sandbox, relative to workspace (required)\n143: \tDestinationPath string `json:\"destinationPath\" validate:\"required\"`\n144: \n145: \t// Overwrite allows overwriting existing files\n146: \tOverwrite bool `json:\"overwrite,omitempty\"`\n147: \n148: \t// ContentType specifies the MIME type (auto-detected if empty)\n149: \tContentType string `json:\"contentType,omitempty\"`\n150: \n151: \t// ChunkSize for chunked uploads (0 for auto-detect)\n152: \tChunkSize int64 `json:\"chunkSize,omitempty\"`\n153: \n154: \t// TotalSize is the known total size (0 if unknown)\n155: \tTotalSize int64 `json:\"totalSize,omitempty\"`\n156: }\n157: \n158: // UploadResult contains the result of a successful upload.\n159: type UploadResult struct {\n160: \t// FileID is a unique identifier for the uploaded file\n161: \tFileID string `json:\"fileId\"`\n162: \n163: \t// Path is the final path in the sandbox\n164: \tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n165: \n166: \t// Size is the uploaded file size in bytes\n167: \tSize int64 `json:\"size\"`\n168: \n169: \t// Checksum is the SHA-256 hash of the file\n170: \tChecksum string `json:\"checksum\"`\n171: \n172: \t// UploadedAt is the timestamp of successful upload\n173: \tUploadedAt time.Time `json:\"uploadedAt\"`\n174: }\n175: \n176: // UploadChunkRequest represents a chunk in a chunked upload.\n177: type UploadChunkRequest struct {\n178: \t// UploadID identifies the upload session\n179: \tUploadID string `json:\"uploadId\" validate:\"required\"`\n180: \n181: \t// ChunkIndex is the 0-based chunk index\n182: \tChunkIndex int `json:\"chunkIndex\" validate:\"gte=0\"`\n183: \n184: \t// ChunkData contains the chunk data\n185: \tChunkData io.Reader `json:\"-\"`\n186: \n187: \t// ChunkSize is the size of this chunk\n188: \tChunkSize int64 `json:\"chunkSize\" validate:\"gt=0\"`\n189: \n190: \t// IsLast indicates this is the final chunk\n191: \tIsLast bool `json:\"isLast\"`\n192: }\n193: \n194: // UploadChunkResult contains the result of a chunk upload.\n195: type UploadChunkResult struct {\n196: \t// ChunkIndex confirms the received chunk index\n197: \tChunkIndex int `json:\"chunkIndex\"`\n198: \n199: \t// ReceivedBytes confirms bytes received\n200: \tReceivedBytes int64 `json:\"receivedBytes\"`\n201: \n202: \t// UploadComplete indicates if the upload is finished\n203: \tUploadComplete bool `json:\"uploadComplete\"`\n204: }\n205: \n206: // Validate validates the upload request.\n207: func (r *UploadRequest) Validate() error {\n208: \tif strings.TrimSpace(r.SessionID) == \"\" {\n209: \t\treturn ErrInvalidSessionID\n210: \t}\n211: \tif strings.TrimSpace(r.SourcePath) == \"\" {\n212: \t\treturn ErrInvalidSourcePath\n213: \t}\n214: \tif strings.TrimSpace(r.DestinationPath) == \"\" {\n215: \t\treturn ErrInvalidDestinationPath\n216: \t}\n217: \tif strings.Contains(r.DestinationPath, \"..\") {\n218: \t\treturn ErrPathTraversal\n219: \t}\n220: \tif filepath.IsAbs(r.DestinationPath) {\n221: \t\treturn ErrPathNotAllowed\n222: \t}\n223: \treturn nil\n224: }\n225: ```\n226: \n227: #### DownloadRequest / DownloadResult\n228: \n229: ```go\n230: // DownloadRequest contains parameters for file download.\n231: type DownloadRequest struct {\n232: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n233: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n234: \n235: \t// Path is the file path in the sandbox (required)\n236: \tPath string `json:\"path\" validate:\"required\"`\n237: \n238: \t// Recursive enables downloading directories as archives\n239: \tRecursive bool `json:\"recursive,omitempty\"`\n240: \n241: \t// ArchiveFormat for recursive downloads: \"zip\", \"tar\", \"tar.gz\"\n242: \tArchiveFormat string `json:\"archiveFormat,omitempty\"`\n243: }\n244: \n245: // DownloadResult contains the result of a successful download.\n246: type DownloadResult struct {\n247: \t// FileID is a unique identifier for the file\n248: \tFileID string `json:\"fileId\"`\n249: \n250: \t// Path is the file path\n251: \tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n252: \n253: \t// Size is the file size in bytes\n254: \tSize int64 `json:\"size\"`\n255: \n256: \t// ContentType is the MIME type\n257: \tContentType string `json:\"contentType\"`\n258: \n259: \t// Data provides a ReadCloser for streaming the file\n260: \tData io.ReadCloser `json:\"-\"`\n261: \n262: \t// Checksum is the SHA-256 hash\n263: \tChecksum string `json:\"checksum\"`\n264: \n265: \t// IsArchive indicates if this is an archive stream\n266: \tIsArchive bool `json:\"isArchive,omitempty\"`\n267: }\n268: \n269: // Validate validates the download request.\n270: func (r *DownloadRequest) Validate() error {\n271: \tif strings.TrimSpace(r.SessionID) == \"\" {\n272: \t\treturn ErrInvalidSessionID\n273: \t}\n274: \tif strings.TrimSpace(r.Path) == \"\" {\n275: \t\treturn ErrInvalidPath\n276: \t}\n277: \tif strings.Contains(r.Path, \"..\") {\n278: \t\treturn ErrPathTraversal\n279: \t}\n280: \tif r.Recursive && r.ArchiveFormat != \"\" {\n281: \t\tvalidFormats := []string{\"zip\", \"tar\", \"tar.gz\"}\n282: \t\tif !slices.Contains(validFormats, r.ArchiveFormat) {\n283: \t\t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: archive format must be zip, tar, or tar.gz\", ErrInvalidRequest)\n284: \t\t}\n285: \t}\n286: \treturn nil\n287: }\n288: ```\n289: \n290: #### ListRequest / ListResult\n291: \n292: ```go\n293: // ListRequest contains parameters for directory listing.\n294: type ListRequest struct {\n295: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n296: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n297: \n298: \t// Path is the directory to list (empty for root)\n299: \tPath string `json:\"path,omitempty\"`\n300: \n301: \t// Recursive lists subdirectories\n302: \tRecursive bool `json:\"recursive,omitempty\"`\n303: \n304: \t// Pattern is a glob pattern for filtering (e.g., \"*.go\")\n305: \tPattern string `json:\"pattern,omitempty\"`\n306: \n307: \t// IncludeHidden includes dotfiles\n308: \tIncludeHidden bool `json:\"includeHidden,omitempty\"`\n309: \n310: \t// Pagination controls result pagination\n311: \tPagination *Pagination `json:\"pagination,omitempty\"`\n312: }\n313: \n314: // Pagination controls list result pagination.\n315: type Pagination struct {\n316: \t// Limit is the maximum number of results\n317: \tLimit int `json:\"limit\" validate:\"gt=0,lte=1000\"`\n318: \n319: \t// Offset is the number of results to skip\n320: \tOffset int `json:\"offset\" validate:\"gte=0\"`\n321: \n322: \t// Cursor is an opaque pagination token\n323: \tCursor string `json:\"cursor,omitempty\"`\n324: }\n325: \n326: // ListResult contains the directory listing.\n327: type ListResult struct {\n328: \t// Entries is the list of file/directory entries\n329: \tEntries []FileInfo `json:\"entries\"`\n330: \n331: \t// TotalCount is the total number of entries (for pagination)\n332: \tTotalCount int `json:\"totalCount\"`\n333: \n334: \t// NextCursor for fetching the next page\n335: \tNextCursor string `json:\"nextCursor,omitempty\"`\n336: }\n337: \n338: // FileInfo represents metadata about a file or directory.\n339: type FileInfo struct {\n340: \t// Name is the entry name\n341: \tName string `json:\"name\"`\n342: \n343: \t// Path is the relative path from workspace root\n344: \tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n345: \n346: \t// Type indicates file, directory, or symlink\n347: \tType FileType `json:\"type\"`\n348: \n349: \t// Size in bytes (files only)\n350: \tSize int64 `json:\"size,omitempty\"`\n351: \n352: \t// Permissions in Unix format\n353: \tPermissions os.FileMode `json:\"permissions\"`\n354: \n355: \t// CreatedAt timestamp\n356: \tCreatedAt time.Time `json:\"createdAt\"`\n357: \n358: \t// ModifiedAt timestamp\n359: \tModifiedAt time.Time `json:\"modifiedAt\"`\n360: \n361: \t// Checksum for files (SHA-256)\n362: \tChecksum string `json:\"checksum,omitempty\"`\n363: \n364: \t// MimeType for files\n365: \tMimeType string `json:\"mimeType,omitempty\"`\n366: }\n367: \n368: // FileType indicates the type of filesystem entry.\n369: type FileType string\n370: \n371: const (\n372: \t// FileTypeFile is a regular file\n373: \tFileTypeFile FileType = \"file\"\n374: \n375: \t// FileTypeDirectory is a directory\n376: \tFileTypeDirectory FileType = \"directory\"\n377: \n378: \t// FileTypeSymlink is a symbolic link\n379: \tFileTypeSymlink FileType = \"symlink\"\n380: )\n381: ```\n382: \n383: #### File Operation Requests\n384: \n385: ```go\n386: // DeleteRequest contains parameters for file deletion.\n387: type DeleteRequest struct {\n388: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n389: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n390: \n391: \t// Path is the file or directory to delete (required)\n392: \tPath string `json:\"path\" validate:\"required\"`\n393: \n394: \t// Recursive deletes directories and contents\n395: \tRecursive bool `json:\"recursive,omitempty\"`\n396: }\n397: \n398: // MoveRequest contains parameters for moving/renaming files.\n399: type MoveRequest struct {\n400: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n401: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n402: \n403: \t// SourcePath is the original path (required)\n404: \tSourcePath string `json:\"sourcePath\" validate:\"required\"`\n405: \n406: \t// DestinationPath is the new path (required)\n407: \tDestinationPath string `json:\"destinationPath\" validate:\"required\"`\n408: \n409: \t// Overwrite allows overwriting existing files\n410: \tOverwrite bool `json:\"overwrite,omitempty\"`\n411: }\n412: \n413: // CopyRequest contains parameters for copying files.\n414: type CopyRequest struct {\n415: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n416: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n417: \n418: \t// SourcePath is the source file path (required)\n419: \tSourcePath string `json:\"sourcePath\" validate:\"required\"`\n420: \n421: \t// DestinationPath is the destination path (required)\n422: \tDestinationPath string `json:\"destinationPath\" validate:\"required\"`\n423: \n424: \t// Overwrite allows overwriting existing files\n425: \tOverwrite bool `json:\"overwrite,omitempty\"`\n426: }\n427: \n428: // MkdirRequest contains parameters for creating directories.\n429: type MkdirRequest struct {\n430: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n431: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n432: \n433: \t// Path is the directory path to create (required)\n434: \tPath string `json:\"path\" validate:\"required\"`\n435: \n436: \t// Permissions for the new directory (default: 0755)\n437: \tPermissions os.FileMode `json:\"permissions,omitempty\"`\n438: \n439: \t// CreateParents creates parent directories if needed\n440: \tCreateParents bool `json:\"createParents,omitempty\"`\n441: }\n442: \n443: // RmdirRequest contains parameters for removing directories.\n444: type RmdirRequest struct {\n445: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n446: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n447: \n448: \t// Path is the directory to remove (required)\n449: \tPath string `json:\"path\" validate:\"required\"`\n450: }\n451: ```\n452: \n453: #### MetadataRequest / FileMetadata\n454: \n455: ```go\n456: // MetadataRequest contains parameters for retrieving file metadata.\n457: type MetadataRequest struct {\n458: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n459: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n460: \n461: \t// Path is the file or directory path (required)\n462: \tPath string `json:\"path\" validate:\"required\"`\n463: }\n464: \n465: // FileMetadata contains comprehensive file metadata.\n466: type FileMetadata struct {\n467: \t// FileInfo contains basic file information\n468: \tFileInfo FileInfo `json:\"fileInfo\"`\n469: \n470: \t// IsReadable indicates read permission\n471: \tIsReadable bool `json:\"isReadable\"`\n472: \n473: \t// IsWritable indicates write permission\n474: \tIsWritable bool `json:\"isWritable\"`\n475: \n476: \t// IsExecutable indicates execute permission\n477: \tIsExecutable bool `json:\"isExecutable\"`\n478: }\n479: ```\n480: \n481: ### Domain Types\n482: \n483: #### QuotaInfo / QuotaManager\n484: \n485: ```go\n486: // QuotaInfo represents storage quota information for a session.\n487: type QuotaInfo struct {\n488: \t// SessionID identifies the session\n489: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\"`\n490: \n491: \t// UsedBytes is the current storage usage\n492: \tUsedBytes int64 `json:\"usedBytes\"`\n493: \n494: \t// TotalBytes is the quota limit (0 for unlimited)\n495: \tTotalBytes int64 `json:\"totalBytes\"`\n496: \n497: \t// AvailableBytes is the remaining quota\n498: \tAvailableBytes int64 `json:\"availableBytes\"`\n499: \n500: \t// FileCount is the current number of files\n501: \tFileCount int64 `json:\"fileCount\"`\n502: \n503: \t// MaxFileCount is the file limit (0 for unlimited)\n504: \tMaxFileCount int64 `json:\"maxFileCount\"`\n505: }\n506: \n507: // QuotaManager defines the interface for quota management.\n508: type QuotaManager interface {\n509: \t// GetQuota retrieves quota information for a session\n510: \tGetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n511: \n512: \t// CheckUpload checks if an upload of size bytes is allowed\n513: \tCheckUpload(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, size int64) error\n514: \n515: \t// UpdateQuota updates quota after a file operation\n516: \tUpdateQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, deltaBytes, deltaFiles int64) error\n517: \n518: \t// SetQuota sets quota limits for a session\n519: \tSetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, totalBytes, maxFileCount int64) error\n520: }\n521: ```\n522: \n523: #### PathValidator\n524: \n525: ```go\n526: // PathValidator validates and sanitizes file paths.\n527: type PathValidator struct {\n528: \t// WorkspaceRoot is the base directory for all operations\n529: \tWorkspaceRoot string\n530: }\n531: \n532: // ValidationResult contains the validated path and metadata.\n533: type ValidationResult struct {\n534: \t// CleanedPath is the sanitized relative path\n535: \tCleanedPath string\n536: \n537: \t// AbsolutePath is the resolved absolute path\n538: \tAbsolutePath string\n539: \n540: \t// IsWithinWorkspace confirms path is inside workspace\n541: \tIsWithinWorkspace bool\n542: }\n543: \n544: // Validate validates a path and returns the resolved result.\n545: func (v *PathValidator) Validate(path string) (*ValidationResult, error) {\n546: \t// Clean the path\n547: \tcleaned := filepath.Clean(path)\n548: \n549: \t// Check for absolute paths\n550: \tif filepath.IsAbs(cleaned) {\n551: \t\treturn nil, ErrPathNotAllowed\n552: \t}\n553: \n554: \t// Check for traversal patterns\n555: \tif strings.Contains(cleaned, \"..\") || strings.HasPrefix(cleaned, \"..\") {\n556: \t\treturn nil, ErrPathTraversal\n557: \t}\n558: \n559: \t// Resolve to absolute path\n560: \tabsPath := filepath.Join(v.WorkspaceRoot, cleaned)\n561: \n562: \t// Verify the path is within workspace (resolves symlinks)\n563: \tresolved, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(absPath)\n564: \tif err != nil && !os.IsNotExist(err) {\n565: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrPathNotAllowed, err)\n566: \t}\n567: \n568: \tif err == nil {\n569: \t\t// Path exists - check it's within workspace\n570: \t\tif !strings.HasPrefix(resolved, v.WorkspaceRoot) {\n571: \t\t\treturn nil, ErrPathTraversal\n572: \t\t}\n573: \t}\n574: \n575: \t// Check parent directories exist and are within workspace\n576: \tdir := filepath.Dir(absPath)\n577: \tif dir != v.WorkspaceRoot {\n578: \t\tresolvedDir, err := filepath.EvalSymlinks(dir)\n579: \t\tif err != nil && !os.IsNotExist(err) {\n580: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrPathNotAllowed, err)\n581: \t\t}\n582: \t\tif err == nil && !strings.HasPrefix(resolvedDir, v.WorkspaceRoot) {\n583: \t\t\treturn nil, ErrPathTraversal\n584: \t\t}\n585: \t}\n586: \n587: \treturn &ValidationResult{\n588: \t\tCleanedPath:       cleaned,\n589: \t\tAbsolutePath:      absPath,\n590: \t\tIsWithinWorkspace: true,\n591: \t}, nil\n592: }\n593: ```\n594: \n595: #### FileWatcher / WatchRequest\n596: \n597: ```go\n598: // WatchRequest contains parameters for file watching.\n599: type WatchRequest struct {\n600: \t// SessionID identifies the target sandbox (required)\n601: \tSessionID string `json:\"sessionId\" validate:\"required\"`\n602: \n603: \t// Path is the directory or file to watch\n604: \tPath string `json:\"path,omitempty\"`\n605: \n606: \t// Recursive watches subdirectories\n607: \tRecursive bool `json:\"recursive,omitempty\"`\n608: \n609: \t// Events filters event types (empty for all)\n610: \tEvents []FileEventType `json:\"events,omitempty\"`\n611: }\n612: \n613: // FileEventType indicates the type of file event.\n614: type FileEventType string\n615: \n616: const (\n617: \t// FileEventCreate indicates a file was created\n618: \tFileEventCreate FileEventType = \"create\"\n619: \n620: \t// FileEventWrite indicates a file was modified\n621: \tFileEventWrite FileEventType = \"write\"\n622: \n623: \t// FileEventRemove indicates a file was removed\n624: \tFileEventRemove FileEventType = \"remove\"\n625: \n626: \t// FileEventRename indicates a file was renamed\n627: \tFileEventRename FileEventType = \"rename\"\n628: \n629: \t// FileEventChmod indicates permissions changed\n630: \tFileEventChmod FileEventType = \"chmod\"\n631: )\n632: \n633: // FileEvent represents a file system event.\n634: type FileEvent struct {\n635: \t// Type is the event type\n636: \tType FileEventType `json:\"type\"`\n637: \n638: \t// Path is the affected file path\n639: \tPath string `json:\"path\"`\n640: \n641: \t// OldPath is the previous path for rename events\n642: \tOldPath string `json:\"oldPath,omitempty\"`\n643: \n644: \t// Timestamp is when the event occurred\n645: \tTimestamp time.Time `json:\"timestamp\"`\n646: }\n647: \n648: // FileWatcher provides file system change notifications.\n649: type FileWatcher interface {\n650: \t// Events returns a channel for file events\n651: \tEvents() <-chan FileEvent\n652: \n653: \t// Errors returns a channel for watch errors\n654: \tErrors() <-chan error\n655: \n656: \t// Stop stops the watcher\n657: \tStop() error\n658: }\n659: ```\n660: \n661: ### Internal Types\n662: \n663: #### FileManager\n664: \n665: ```go\n666: // FileManager defines the interface for file operations in sandboxes.\n667: type FileManager interface {\n668: \t// Upload uploads a file to the sandbox\n669: \tUpload(ctx context.Context, req UploadRequest) (*UploadResult, error)\n670: \n671: \t// UploadChunk uploads a chunk in a chunked upload\n672: \tUploadChunk(ctx context.Context, req UploadChunkRequest) (*UploadChunkResult, error)\n673: \n674: \t// Download downloads a file from the sandbox\n675: \tDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (*DownloadResult, error)\n676: \n677: \t// StreamDownload returns a ReadCloser for streaming download\n678: \tStreamDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n679: \n680: \t// List lists directory contents\n681: \tList(ctx context.Context, req ListRequest) (*ListResult, error)\n682: \n683: \t// Delete deletes a file or directory\n684: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, req DeleteRequest) error\n685: \n686: \t// Move moves/renames a file or directory\n687: \tMove(ctx context.Context, req MoveRequest) error\n688: \n689: \t// Copy copies a file or directory\n690: \tCopy(ctx context.Context, req CopyRequest) error\n691: \n692: \t// Mkdir creates a directory\n693: \tMkdir(ctx context.Context, req MkdirRequest) error\n694: \n695: \t// Rmdir removes a directory\n696: \tRmdir(ctx context.Context, req RmdirRequest) error\n697: \n698: \t// GetMetadata retrieves file metadata\n699: \tGetMetadata(ctx context.Context, req MetadataRequest) (*FileMetadata, error)\n700: \n701: \t// SetPermissions sets file permissions\n702: \tSetPermissions(ctx context.Context, sessionID, path string, mode os.FileMode) error\n703: \n704: \t// GetQuota retrieves quota information\n705: \tGetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n706: \n707: \t// Watch starts watching a path for changes\n708: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, req WatchRequest) (FileWatcher, error)\n709: }\n710: \n711: // fileManager implements FileManager.\n712: type fileManager struct {\n713: \t// validator validates file paths\n714: \tvalidator *PathValidator\n715: \n716: \t// quotaManager manages storage quotas\n717: \tquotaManager QuotaManager\n718: \n719: \t// sandboxResolver resolves session IDs\n720: \tsandboxResolver SandboxResolver\n721: \n722: \t// uploadSessions tracks active chunked uploads\n723: \tuploadSessions map[string]*uploadSession\n724: \n725: \t// mu protects uploadSessions\n726: \tmu sync.RWMutex\n727: \n728: \t// config contains file manager configuration\n729: \tconfig FileManagerConfig\n730: }\n731: \n732: // uploadSession tracks state for chunked uploads.\n733: type uploadSession struct {\n734: \tID            string\n735: \tSessionID     string\n736: \tDestination   string\n737: \tTotalSize     int64\n738: \tReceivedBytes int64\n739: \tChunkSize     int64\n740: \tChunks        map[int]bool\n741: \tTempDir       string\n742: \tCreatedAt     time.Time\n743: \tLastActivity  time.Time\n744: }\n745: ```\n746: \n747: #### FileManagerConfig\n748: \n749: ```go\n750: // FileManagerConfig contains configuration for FileManager.\n751: type FileManagerConfig struct {\n752: \t// MaxUploadSize is the maximum allowed upload size (default: 1GB)\n753: \tMaxUploadSize int64\n754: \n755: \t// MaxChunkSize is the maximum chunk size for uploads (default: 64MB)\n756: \tMaxChunkSize int64\n757: \n758: \t// DefaultChunkSize is the default chunk size (default: 16MB)\n759: \tDefaultChunkSize int64\n760: \n761: \t// UploadSessionTimeout is how long to keep incomplete upload sessions (default: 1h)\n762: \tUploadSessionTimeout time.Duration\n763: \n764: \t// MaxConcurrentUploads limits concurrent uploads per session (default: 5)\n765: \tMaxConcurrentUploads int\n766: \n767: \t// MaxConcurrentDownloads limits concurrent downloads per session (default: 5)\n768: \tMaxConcurrentDownloads int\n769: \n770: \t// StreamBufferSize is the buffer size for streaming (default: 32KB)\n771: \tStreamBufferSize int\n772: \n773: \t// ArchiveCompressionLevel for zip/tar.gz archives (default: 6)\n774: \tArchiveCompressionLevel int\n775: }\n776: \n777: // DefaultFileManagerConfig returns default configuration.\n778: func DefaultFileManagerConfig() FileManagerConfig {\n779: \treturn FileManagerConfig{\n780: \t\tMaxUploadSize:           1024 * 1024 * 1024, // 1GB\n781: \t\tMaxChunkSize:            64 * 1024 * 1024,   // 64MB\n782: \t\tDefaultChunkSize:        16 * 1024 * 1024,   // 16MB\n783: \t\tUploadSessionTimeout:    time.Hour,\n784: \t\tMaxConcurrentUploads:    5,\n785: \t\tMaxConcurrentDownloads:  5,\n786: \t\tStreamBufferSize:        32 * 1024, // 32KB\n787: \t\tArchiveCompressionLevel: 6,\n788: \t}\n789: }\n790: \n791: // ConfigFromEnv loads configuration from environment variables.\n792: func ConfigFromEnv() FileManagerConfig {\n793: \tcfg := DefaultFileManagerConfig()\n794: \n795: \tif v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_MAX_UPLOAD_SIZE\"); v != \"\" {\n796: \t\tif n, err := strconv.ParseInt(v, 10, 64); err == nil {\n797: \t\t\tcfg.MaxUploadSize = n\n798: \t\t}\n799: \t}\n800: \tif v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_MAX_CHUNK_SIZE\"); v != \"\" {\n801: \t\tif n, err := strconv.ParseInt(v, 10, 64); err == nil {\n802: \t\t\tcfg.MaxChunkSize = n\n803: \t\t}\n804: \t}\n805: \tif v := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_UPLOAD_SESSION_TIMEOUT\"); v != \"\" {\n806: \t\tif d, err := time.ParseDuration(v); err == nil {\n807: \t\t\tcfg.UploadSessionTimeout = d\n808: \t\t}\n809: \t}\n810: \n811: \treturn cfg\n812: }\n813: ```\n814: \n815: ### Constants\n816: \n817: ```go\n818: // Default configuration values\n819: const (\n820: \t// DefaultMaxUploadSize is 1GB\n821: \tDefaultMaxUploadSize = 1024 * 1024 * 1024\n822: \n823: \t// DefaultChunkSize is 16MB\n824: \tDefaultChunkSize = 16 * 1024 * 1024\n825: \n826: \t// DefaultStreamBufferSize is 32KB\n827: \tDefaultStreamBufferSize = 32 * 1024\n828: \n829: \t// UploadIDLength is the length of generated upload IDs\n830: \tUploadIDLength = 16\n831: \n832: \t// UploadIDPrefix is the prefix for upload IDs\n833: \tUploadIDPrefix = \"upload-\"\n834: \n835: \t// FileIDLength is the length of generated file IDs\n836: \tFileIDLength = 16\n837: \n838: \t// FileIDPrefix is the prefix for file IDs\n839: \tFileIDPrefix = \"file-\"\n840: )\n841: \n842: // Error codes\n843: const (\n844: \t// ErrorCodeInvalidRequest indicates malformed request\n845: \tErrorCodeInvalidRequest = \"INVALID_REQUEST\"\n846: \n847: \t// ErrorCodeInvalidSessionID indicates missing or invalid session ID\n848: \tErrorCodeInvalidSessionID = \"INVALID_SESSION_ID\"\n849: \n850: \t// ErrorCodeInvalidPath indicates invalid path\n851: \tErrorCodeInvalidPath = \"INVALID_PATH\"\n852: \n853: \t// ErrorCodePathTraversal indicates path traversal attempt\n854: \tErrorCodePathTraversal = \"PATH_TRAVERSAL\"\n855: \n856: \t// ErrorCodePathNotAllowed indicates path outside workspace\n857: \tErrorCodePathNotAllowed = \"PATH_NOT_ALLOWED\"\n858: \n859: \t// ErrorCodeFileNotFound indicates file does not exist\n860: \tErrorCodeFileNotFound = \"FILE_NOT_FOUND\"\n861: \n862: \t// ErrorCodeFileExists indicates file already exists\n863: \tErrorCodeFileExists = \"FILE_EXISTS\"\n864: \n865: \t// ErrorCodeIsDirectory indicates expected file but got directory\n866: \tErrorCodeIsDirectory = \"IS_DIRECTORY\"\n867: \n868: \t// ErrorCodeNotDirectory indicates expected directory but got file\n869: \tErrorCodeNotDirectory = \"NOT_DIRECTORY\"\n870: \n871: \t// ErrorCodeDirectoryNotEmpty indicates non-empty directory deletion\n872: \tErrorCodeDirectoryNotEmpty = \"DIRECTORY_NOT_EMPTY\"\n873: \n874: \t// ErrorCodeQuotaExceeded indicates storage quota exceeded\n875: \tErrorCodeQuotaExceeded = \"QUOTA_EXCEEDED\"\n876: \n877: \t// ErrorCodePermissionDenied indicates insufficient permissions\n878: \tErrorCodePermissionDenied = \"PERMISSION_DENIED\"\n879: \n880: \t// ErrorCodeTransferFailed indicates upload/download failure\n881: \tErrorCodeTransferFailed = \"TRANSFER_FAILED\"\n882: \n883: \t// ErrorCodeChecksumMismatch indicates checksum verification failed\n884: \tErrorCodeChecksumMismatch = \"CHECKSUM_MISMATCH\"\n885: \n886: \t// ErrorCodeSandboxUnavailable indicates sandbox not accessible\n887: \tErrorCodeSandboxUnavailable = \"SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE\"\n888: \n889: \t// ErrorCodeUploadSessionNotFound indicates upload session expired/invalid\n890: \tErrorCodeUploadSessionNotFound = \"UPLOAD_SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"\n891: \n892: \t// ErrorCodeUploadSessionExpired indicates upload session timeout\n893: \tErrorCodeUploadSessionExpired = \"UPLOAD_SESSION_EXPIRED\"\n894: )\n895: ```\n896: \n897: ---\n898: \n899: ## API Contracts\n900: \n901: ### FileManager Interface\n902: \n903: ```go\n904: // FileManager is the primary API for PicoD file operations.\n905: type FileManager interface {\n906: \t// Upload uploads a file to the sandbox.\n907: \t//\n908: \t// Parameters:\n909: \t//   - ctx: Context for cancellation and timeouts\n910: \t//   - req: Upload request containing source, destination, and options\n911: \t//\n912: \t// Returns:\n913: \t//   - *UploadResult: Result containing file ID, size, and checksum\n914: \t//   - error: ErrInvalidRequest, ErrPathTraversal, ErrQuotaExceeded, etc.\n915: \tUpload(ctx context.Context, req UploadRequest) (*UploadResult, error)\n916: \n917: \t// UploadChunk uploads a chunk in a chunked upload session.\n918: \t//\n919: \t// Parameters:\n920: \t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n921: \t//   - req: Chunk upload request with upload ID and chunk data\n922: \t//\n923: \t// Returns:\n924: \t//   - *UploadChunkResult: Result containing completion status\n925: \t//   - error: ErrUploadSessionNotFound, ErrChecksumMismatch, etc.\n926: \tUploadChunk(ctx context.Context, req UploadChunkRequest) (*UploadChunkResult, error)\n927: \n928: \t// Download downloads a file from the sandbox.\n929: \t//\n930: \t// Parameters:\n931: \t//   - ctx: Context for cancellation and timeouts\n932: \t//   - req: Download request containing path and options\n933: \t//\n934: \t// Returns:\n935: \t//   - *DownloadResult: Result with file metadata and io.ReadCloser\n936: \t//   - error: ErrFileNotFound, ErrIsDirectory, etc.\n937: \tDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (*DownloadResult, error)\n938: \n939: \t// StreamDownload returns a ReadCloser for streaming file download.\n940: \t//\n941: \t// Parameters:\n942: \t//   - ctx: Context for the streaming operation\n943: \t//   - req: Download request\n944: \t//\n945: \t// Returns:\n946: \t//   - io.ReadCloser: Stream for reading file data\n947: \t//   - error: ErrFileNotFound, ErrSandboxUnavailable, etc.\n948: \tStreamDownload(ctx context.Context, req DownloadRequest) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n949: \n950: \t// List lists directory contents with optional filtering and pagination.\n951: \t//\n952: \t// Parameters:\n953: \t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n954: \t//   - req: List request containing path and options\n955: \t//\n956: \t// Returns:\n957: \t//   - *ListResult: Result containing file entries and pagination info\n958: \t//   - error: ErrFileNotFound, ErrNotDirectory, etc.\n959: \tList(ctx context.Context, req ListRequest) (*ListResult, error)\n960: \n961: \t// Delete deletes a file or directory.\n962: \t//\n963: \t// Parameters:\n964: \t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n965: \t//   - req: Delete request containing path and options\n966: \t//\n967: \t// Returns:\n968: \t//   - error: nil on success, ErrFileNotFound, ErrDirectoryNotEmpty, etc.\n969: \tDelete(ctx context.Context, req DeleteRequest) error\n970: \n971: \t// Move moves/renames a file or directory.\n972: \t//\n973: \t// Parameters:\n974: \t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n975: \t//   - req: Move request containing source and destination\n976: \t//\n977: \t// Returns:\n978: \t//   - error: nil on success, ErrFileNotFound, ErrFileExists, etc.\n979: \tMove(ctx context.Context, req MoveRequest) error\n980: \n981: \t// Copy copies a file or directory.\n982: \t//\n983: \t// Parameters:\n984: \t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n985: \t//   - req: Copy request containing source and destination\n986: \t//\n987: \t// Returns:\n988: \t//   - error: nil on success, ErrFileNotFound, ErrQuotaExceeded, etc.\n989: \tCopy(ctx context.Context, req CopyRequest) error\n990: \n991: \t// Mkdir creates a directory.\n992: \t//\n993: \t// Parameters:\n994: \t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n995: \t//   - req: Mkdir request containing path and permissions\n996: \t//\n997: \t// Returns:\n998: \t//   - error: nil on success, ErrFileExists, ErrPathTraversal, etc.\n999: \tMkdir(ctx context.Context, req MkdirRequest) error\n1000: \n1001: \t// Rmdir removes a directory (must be empty unless recursive).\n1002: \t//\n1003: \t// Parameters:\n1004: \t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n1005: \t//   - req: Rmdir request containing path\n1006: \t//\n1007: \t// Returns:\n1008: \t//   - error: nil on success, ErrDirectoryNotEmpty, etc.\n1009: \tRmdir(ctx context.Context, req RmdirRequest) error\n1010: \n1011: \t// GetMetadata retrieves file metadata.\n1012: \t//\n1013: \t// Parameters:\n1014: \t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n1015: \t//   - req: Metadata request containing path\n1016: \t//\n1017: \t// Returns:\n1018: \t//   - *FileMetadata: Metadata including permissions and info\n1019: \t//   - error: ErrFileNotFound, etc.\n1020: \tGetMetadata(ctx context.Context, req MetadataRequest) (*FileMetadata, error)\n1021: \n1022: \t// SetPermissions sets file permissions.\n1023: \t//\n1024: \t// Parameters:\n1025: \t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n1026: \t//   - sessionID: Target session ID\n1027: \t//   - path: File path\n1028: \t//   - mode: New permissions\n1029: \t//\n1030: \t// Returns:\n1031: \t//   - error: nil on success, ErrFileNotFound, ErrPermissionDenied, etc.\n1032: \tSetPermissions(ctx context.Context, sessionID, path string, mode os.FileMode) error\n1033: \n1034: \t// GetQuota retrieves quota information for a session.\n1035: \t//\n1036: \t// Parameters:\n1037: \t//   - ctx: Context for the operation\n1038: \t//   - sessionID: Target session ID\n1039: \t//\n1040: \t// Returns:\n1041: \t//   - *QuotaInfo: Quota usage and limits\n1042: \t//   - error: ErrSandboxUnavailable, etc.\n1043: \tGetQuota(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n1044: \n1045: \t// Watch starts watching a path for file system changes.\n1046: \t//\n1047: \t// Parameters:\n1048: \t//   - ctx: Context for the watch lifecycle\n1049: \t//   - req: Watch request containing path and event filters\n1050: \t//\n1051: \t// Returns:\n1052: \t//   - FileWatcher: Watcher for receiving events\n1053: \t//   - error: ErrFileNotFound, etc.\n1054: \tWatch(ctx context.Context, req WatchRequest) (FileWatcher, error)\n1055: }\n1056: ```\n1057: \n1058: ### Service Interfaces\n1059: \n1060: ```go\n1061: // SandboxResolver resolves session IDs to sandbox information.\n1062: type SandboxResolver interface {\n1063: \t// Resolve returns sandbox info for a session ID.\n1064: \t// Returns ErrSandboxNotFound if session doesn't exist.\n1065: \tResolve(ctx context.Context, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)\n1066: }\n1067: \n1068: // SandboxFileOps performs file operations in a sandbox.\n1069: type SandboxFileOps interface {\n1070: \t// ReadFile reads a file from the sandbox\n1071: \tReadFile(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string) (io.ReadCloser, error)\n1072: \n1073: \t// WriteFile writes a file to the sandbox\n1074: \tWriteFile(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string, reader io.Reader, size int64) error\n1075: \n1076: \t// DeleteFile deletes a file or directory\n1077: \tDeleteFile(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string, recursive bool) error\n1078: \n1079: \t// MoveFile moves/renames a file\n1080: \tMoveFile(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, src, dst string) error\n1081: \n1082: \t// CopyFile copies a file\n1083: \tCopyFile(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, src, dst string) error\n1084: \n1085: \t// ListDirectory lists directory contents\n1086: \tListDirectory(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string, recursive bool) ([]FileInfo, error)\n1087: \n1088: \t// CreateDirectory creates a directory\n1089: \tCreateDirectory(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string, mode os.FileMode, parents bool) error\n1090: \n1091: \t// RemoveDirectory removes a directory\n1092: \tRemoveDirectory(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string) error\n1093: \n1094: \t// GetFileInfo retrieves file information\n1095: \tGetFileInfo(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string) (*FileInfo, error)\n1096: \n1097: \t// SetPermissions sets file permissions\n1098: \tSetPermissions(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, path string, mode os.FileMode) error\n1099: \n1100: \t// GetDiskUsage retrieves disk usage for the sandbox\n1101: \tGetDiskUsage(ctx context.Context, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo) (*QuotaInfo, error)\n1102: }\n1103: \n1104: // PicoDService provides high-level PicoD operations.\n1105: type PicoDService interface {\n1106: \t// FileManager returns the file manager.\n1107: \tFileManager() FileManager\n1108: \n1109: \t// CommandExecutor returns the command executor (from AR-015).\n1110: \tCommandExecutor() CommandExecutor\n1111: \n1112: \t// Health returns the service health status.\n1113: \tHealth(ctx context.Context) error\n1114: \n1115: \t// Shutdown gracefully shuts down the service.\n1116: \tShutdown(ctx context.Context) error\n1117: }\n1118: ```\n1119: \n1120: ---\n1121: \n1122: ## Error Handling\n1123: \n1124: ### Error Categories and Codes\n1125: \n1126: | Error | Code | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n1127: |-------|------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n1128: | `ErrInvalidRequest` | `INVALID_REQUEST` | Malformed file operation request | No | Return with field details |\n1129: | `ErrInvalidSessionID` | `INVALID_SESSION_ID` | Missing or invalid session ID | No | Return 400 |\n1130: | `ErrInvalidPath` | `INVALID_PATH` | Empty or invalid path | No | Return 400 |\n1131: | `ErrPathTraversal` | `PATH_TRAVERSAL` | Detected path traversal attempt | No | Return 403, log security event |\n1132: | `ErrPathNotAllowed` | `PATH_NOT_ALLOWED` | Path outside workspace | No | Return 403 |\n1133: | `ErrFileNotFound` | `FILE_NOT_FOUND` | Specified path does not exist | No | Return 404 |\n1134: | `ErrFileExists` | `FILE_EXISTS` | File already exists (no overwrite) | No | Return 409 |\n1135: | `ErrIsDirectory` | `IS_DIRECTORY` | Expected file but got directory | No | Return 400 |\n1136: | `ErrNotDirectory` | `NOT_DIRECTORY` | Expected directory but got file | No | Return 400 |\n1137: | `ErrDirectoryNotEmpty` | `DIRECTORY_NOT_EMPTY` | Cannot delete non-empty dir | No | Return 400 |\n1138: | `ErrQuotaExceeded` | `QUOTA_EXCEEDED` | Storage quota limit reached | No | Return 413 |\n1139: | `ErrPermissionDenied` | `PERMISSION_DENIED` | Insufficient permissions | No | Return 403 |\n1140: | `ErrTransferFailed` | `TRANSFER_FAILED` | Upload/download operation failed | Yes | Retry with backoff |\n1141: | `ErrChecksumMismatch` | `CHECKSUM_MISMATCH` | Data integrity check failed | Yes | Retry upload |\n1142: | `ErrSandboxUnavailable` | `SANDBOX_UNAVAILABLE` | Sandbox not accessible | Yes | Retry with backoff |\n1143: | `ErrUploadSessionNotFound` | `UPLOAD_SESSION_NOT_FOUND` | Invalid upload session | No | Return 404 |\n1144: | `ErrUploadSessionExpired` | `UPLOAD_SESSION_EXPIRED` | Upload session timeout | No | Return 410 |\n1145: \n1146: ### Sentinel Errors\n1147: \n1148: ```go\n1149: // PicoD file operation errors\n1150: var (\n1151: \tErrInvalidRequest              = errors.New(\"picod: invalid request\")\n1152: \tErrInvalidSessionID            = errors.New(\"picod: session ID is required\")\n1153: \tErrInvalidSourcePath           = errors.New(\"picod: source path is required\")\n1154: \tErrInvalidDestinationPath      = errors.New(\"picod: destination path is required\")\n1155: \tErrInvalidPath                 = errors.New(\"picod: path is required\")\n1156: \tErrPathTraversal               = errors.New(\"picod: path traversal detected\")\n1157: \tErrPathNotAllowed              = errors.New(\"picod: path outside workspace\")\n1158: \tErrFileNotFound                = errors.New(\"picod: file not found\")\n1159: \tErrFileExists                  = errors.New(\"picod: file already exists\")\n1160: \tErrIsDirectory                 = errors.New(\"picod: path is a directory\")\n1161: \tErrNotDirectory                = errors.New(\"picod: path is not a directory\")\n1162: \tErrDirectoryNotEmpty           = errors.New(\"picod: directory not empty\")\n1163: \tErrQuotaExceeded               = errors.New(\"picod: storage quota exceeded\")\n1164: \tErrPermissionDenied            = errors.New(\"picod: permission denied\")\n1165: \tErrTransferFailed              = errors.New(\"picod: file transfer failed\")\n1166: \tErrChecksumMismatch            = errors.New(\"picod: checksum verification failed\")\n1167: \tErrSandboxUnavailable          = errors.New(\"picod: sandbox unavailable\")\n1168: \tErrUploadSessionNotFound       = errors.New(\"picod: upload session not found\")\n1169: \tErrUploadSessionExpired        = errors.New(\"picod: upload session expired\")\n1170: )\n1171: ```\n1172: \n1173: ### FileError Structure\n1174: \n1175: ```go\n1176: // FileError represents a file operation error with context.\n1177: type FileError struct {\n1178: \t// Code is the machine-readable error code\n1179: \tCode string `json:\"code\"`\n1180: \n1181: \t// Message is the human-readable error message\n1182: \tMessage string `json:\"message\"`\n1183: \n1184: \t// Path is the file path related to the error\n1185: \tPath string `json:\"path,omitempty\"`\n1186: \n1187: \t// Details contains additional error context\n1188: \tDetails map[string]interface{} `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n1189: }\n1190: \n1191: // Error returns the error string.\n1192: func (e *FileError) Error() string {\n1193: \tif e.Path != \"\" {\n1194: \t\treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (path=%s)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Path)\n1195: \t}\n1196: \treturn fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", e.Code, e.Message)\n1197: }\n1198: \n1199: // NewFileError creates a new FileError.\n1200: func NewFileError(code, message, path string) *FileError {\n1201: \treturn &FileError{\n1202: \t\tCode:    code,\n1203: \t\tMessage: message,\n1204: \t\tPath:    path,\n1205: \t}\n1206: }\n1207: \n1208: // WithDetails adds details to the error.\n1209: func (e *FileError) WithDetails(details map[string]interface{}) *FileError {\n1210: \te.Details = details\n1211: \treturn e\n1212: }\n1213: ```\n1214: \n1215: ### Error Handling Patterns\n1216: \n1217: #### Upload Error Handling\n1218: \n1219: ```go\n1220: func (fm *fileManager) Upload(ctx context.Context, req UploadRequest) (*UploadResult, error) {\n1221: \t// Validate request\n1222: \tif err := req.Validate(); err != nil {\n1223: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrInvalidRequest, err)\n1224: \t}\n1225: \n1226: \t// Validate path\n1227: \tpathResult, err := fm.validator.Validate(req.DestinationPath)\n1228: \tif err != nil {\n1229: \t\treturn nil, err\n1230: \t}\n1231: \n1232: \t// Check if file exists (and overwrite not allowed)\n1233: \tif !req.Overwrite {\n1234: \t\texists, err := fm.fileExists(ctx, req.SessionID, pathResult.AbsolutePath)\n1235: \t\tif err != nil {\n1236: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: failed to check file existence: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n1237: \t\t}\n1238: \t\tif exists {\n1239: \t\t\treturn nil, NewFileError(ErrorCodeFileExists, \"file already exists\", req.DestinationPath)\n1240: \t\t}\n1241: \t}\n1242: \n1243: \t// Check quota if size is known\n1244: \tif req.TotalSize > 0 {\n1245: \t\tif err := fm.quotaManager.CheckUpload(ctx, req.SessionID, req.TotalSize); err != nil {\n1246: \t\t\treturn nil, err\n1247: \t\t}\n1248: \t}\n1249: \n1250: \t// Resolve sandbox\n1251: \tsandbox, err := fm.sandboxResolver.Resolve(ctx, req.SessionID)\n1252: \tif err != nil {\n1253: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n1254: \t}\n1255: \n1256: \t// Perform upload with timeout\n1257: \tuploadCtx, cancel := context.WithTimeout(ctx, fm.config.UploadSessionTimeout)\n1258: \tdefer cancel()\n1259: \n1260: \tresult, err := fm.performUpload(uploadCtx, sandbox, req, pathResult)\n1261: \tif err != nil {\n1262: \t\tif errors.Is(err, context.DeadlineExceeded) {\n1263: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: upload timeout exceeded\", ErrTransferFailed)\n1264: \t\t}\n1265: \t\tif errors.Is(err, context.Canceled) {\n1266: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: upload was cancelled\", ErrTransferFailed)\n1267: \t\t}\n1268: \t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrTransferFailed, err)\n1269: \t}\n1270: \n1271: \t// Update quota\n1272: \tif err := fm.quotaManager.UpdateQuota(ctx, req.SessionID, result.Size, 1); err != nil {\n1273: \t\t// Log but don't fail - quota will be consistent on next check\n1274: \t\tlog.Printf(\"warning: failed to update quota: %v\", err)\n1275: \t}\n1276: \n1277: \treturn result, nil\n1278: }\n1279: ```\n1280: \n1281: #### Path Validation Error Handling\n1282: \n1283: ```go\n1284: func (fm *fileManager) validatePath(ctx context.Context, sessionID, path string, mustExist bool) (*ValidationResult, error) {\n1285: \t// Validate path format\n1286: \tresult, err := fm.validator.Validate(path)\n1287: \tif err != nil {\n1288: \t\tif errors.Is(err, ErrPathTraversal) {\n1289: \t\t\t// Log security event\n1290: \t\t\tfm.logSecurityEvent(ctx, sessionID, \"path_traversal_attempt\", map[string]string{\n1291: \t\t\t\t\"path\": path,\n1292: \t\t\t})\n1293: \t\t\treturn nil, NewFileError(ErrorCodePathTraversal, \"path traversal detected\", path)\n1294: \t\t}\n1295: \t\tif errors.Is(err, ErrPathNotAllowed) {\n1296: \t\t\treturn nil, NewFileError(ErrorCodePathNotAllowed, \"path outside workspace\", path)\n1297: \t\t}\n1298: \t\treturn nil, err\n1299: \t}\n1300: \n1301: \t// Check existence if required\n1302: \tif mustExist {\n1303: \t\texists, err := fm.fileExists(ctx, sessionID, result.AbsolutePath)\n1304: \t\tif err != nil {\n1305: \t\t\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: failed to check file: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n1306: \t\t}\n1307: \t\tif !exists {\n1308: \t\t\treturn nil, NewFileError(ErrorCodeFileNotFound, \"file not found\", path)\n1309: \t\t}\n1310: \t}\n1311: \n1312: \treturn result, nil\n1313: }\n1314: ```\n1315: \n1316: #### Quota Enforcement\n1317: \n1318: ```go\n1319: func (qm *quotaManager) CheckUpload(ctx context.Context, sessionID string, size int64) error {\n1320: \tquota, err := qm.GetQuota(ctx, sessionID)\n1321: \tif err != nil {\n1322: \t\treturn fmt.Errorf(\"%w: failed to get quota: %v\", ErrSandboxUnavailable, err)\n1323: \t}\n1324: \n1325: \t// Check total bytes limit\n1326: \tif quota.TotalBytes > 0 && size > quota.AvailableBytes {\n1327: \t\treturn NewFileError(ErrorCodeQuotaExceeded,\n1328: \t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"upload size %d exceeds available quota %d\", size, quota.AvailableBytes),\n1329: \t\t\t\"\").\n1330: \t\t\tWithDetails(map[string]interface{}{\n1331: \t\t\t\t\"requested\": size,\n1332: \t\t\t\t\"available\": quota.AvailableBytes,\n1333: \t\t\t\t\"total\":     quota.TotalBytes,\n1334: \t\t\t})\n1335: \t}\n1336: \n1337: \t// Check file count limit\n1338: \tif quota.MaxFileCount > 0 && quota.FileCount >= quota.MaxFileCount {\n1339: \t\treturn NewFileError(ErrorCodeQuotaExceeded,\n1340: \t\t\tfmt.Sprintf(\"file count limit %d reached\", quota.MaxFileCount),\n1341: \t\t\t\"\").\n1342: \t\t\tWithDetails(map[string]interface{}{\n1343: \t\t\t\t\"current\": quota.FileCount,\n1344: \t\t\t\t\"limit\":   quota.MaxFileCount,\n1345: \t\t\t})\n1346: \t}\n1347: \n1348: \treturn nil\n1349: }\n1350: ```\n1351: \n1352: ---\n1353: \n1354: ## Testing Strategy\n1355: \n1356: ### Unit Tests\n1357: \n1358: ```go\n1359: func TestFileManager_Upload_Success(t *testing.T) {\n1360: \t// Setup mocks\n1361: \tmockQuota := new(mockQuotaManager)\n1362: \tmockResolver := new(mockSandboxResolver)\n1363: \tmockSandboxOps := new(mockSandboxFileOps)\n1364: \n1365: \tfm := NewFileManager(FileManagerConfig{}, mockQuota, mockResolver, mockSandboxOps)\n1366: \n1367: \t// Setup expectations\n1368: \tsandbox := &types.SandboxInfo{\n1369: \t\tSessionID: \"sess-123\",\n1370: \t\tPodIP:     \"10.0.0.1\",\n1371: \t}\n1372: \tmockResolver.On(\"Resolve\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\").Return(sandbox, nil)\n1373: \tmockQuota.On(\"CheckUpload\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\", int64(1024)).Return(nil)\n1374: \tmockSandboxOps.On(\"WriteFile\", mock.Anything, sandbox, \"/workspace/test.txt\", mock.Anything, int64(1024)).Return(nil)\n1375: \tmockQuota.On(\"UpdateQuota\", mock.Anything, \"sess-123\", int64(1024), int64(1)).Return(nil)\n1376: \n1377: \t// Execute\n1378: \tresult, err := fm.Upload(context.Background(), UploadRequest{\n1379: \t\tSessionID:       \"sess-123\",\n1380: \t\tSourcePath:      \"/tmp/test.txt\",\n1381: \t\tDestinationPath: \"test.txt\",\n1382: \t\tTotalSize:       1024,\n1383: \t})\n1384: \n1385: \t// Assert\n1386: \tassert.NoError(t, err)\n1387: \tassert.NotEmpty(t, result.FileID)\n1388: \tassert.Equal(t, \"test.txt\", result.Path)\n1389: \tassert.Equal(t, int64(1024), result.Size)\n1390: \tmockResolver.AssertExpectations(t)\n1391: \tmockQuota.AssertExpectations(t)\n1392: \tmockSandboxOps.AssertExpectations(t)\n1393: }\n1394: \n1395: func TestFileManager_Upload_PathTraversal(t *testing.T) {\n\n(Output capped at 50 KB. Showing lines 1-1395. Use offset=1396 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-016 Design: PicoD File Management API\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-016  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** M (Medium)\n\nThe PicoD File Management API provides a unified interface for file operations within sandboxed environments. It supports file upload/download, directory listing, file operations (create, delete, move, copy), path security enforcement, and quota management.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **Sandbox Interface (AR-009)**: For actual file operations in sandbox environments\n- **Status Store (AR-012/AR-013/AR-014)**: For operation tracking and quota persistence\n- **PicoD Command Execution (AR-015)**: For complementary command-based file operations\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775877934853,"end":1775877934885}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877934891,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a92c938001Zv9iLJmRWTeDTq","messageID":"msg_d7a9290250017FrAY3CuGOfCM4","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Proposal: PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n4: \n5: | Field | Value |\n6: |-------|-------|\n7: | **Module** | `pkg/picod/jwt` |\n8: | **Language** | Go |\n9: | **Size** | S (Small) |\n10: | **Status** | Proposed |\n11: \n12: ---\n13: \n14: ## Purpose\n15: \n16: Implement the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer that provides secure token-based authentication for agentcube platform endpoints. This proposal delivers:\n17: \n18: 1. **Token Validation**: Support for HS256 (HMAC-SHA256) and RS256 (RSA-SHA256) JWT signature verification\n19: 2. **Claims Validation**: Verification of standard claims including expiration (`exp`), issuer (`iss`), and issued-at (`iat`) with configurable clock skew tolerance\n20: 3. **HTTP Middleware**: Injectable middleware for HTTP handlers that extracts and validates Bearer tokens from Authorization headers\n21: 4. **Configuration Management**: Environment-based configuration for JWT secrets, public keys, issuer validation, and algorithm selection\n22: 5. **Context Integration**: Propagation of parsed claims through request context for downstream handlers\n23: 6. **Standardized Error Responses**: Consistent HTTP 401/403 responses for authentication and authorization failures\n24: \n25: This middleware integrates with the PicoD command execution API (AR-015) to provide a secure authentication layer, ensuring only valid, trusted requests are processed by the agentcube platform.\n26: \n27: ---\n28: \n29: ## Scope\n30: \n31: ### In Scope\n32: \n33: | Item | Detail |\n34: |------|--------|\n35: | **JWTValidator Interface** | Core interface for token validation with multiple algorithms |\n36: | **HS256 Support** | HMAC-SHA256 signature verification using shared secrets |\n37: | **RS256 Support** | RSA-SHA256 signature verification using public keys |\n38: | **Token Parsing** | JWT token parsing with header and claims extraction |\n39: | **Claims Validation** | Standard claims validation (exp, iss, iat) with clock skew |\n40: | **HTTP Middleware** | Injectable middleware for HTTP handlers |\n41: | **Bearer Token Extraction** | Authorization header parsing with Bearer scheme |\n42: | **Context Propagation** | Claims injection into request context |\n43: | **Configuration Loading** | Environment variable-based configuration |\n44: | **Error Types** | Domain-specific errors for validation failures |\n45: | **HTTP Responses** | Standardized JSON error responses (401/403) |\n46: \n47: ### Out of Scope\n48: \n49: - Token generation/issuance (handled by external identity provider)\n50: - Refresh token mechanism\n51: - OAuth2/OIDC integration\n52: - Session management\n53: - Rate limiting (separate middleware)\n54: - Audit logging (handled by separate layer)\n55: - JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) support (future enhancement)\n56: - Audience claim validation (future enhancement)\n57: - Multiple issuer support (future enhancement)\n58: \n59: ---\n60: \n61: ## Design\n62: \n63: ### File Structure\n64: \n65: | File | Role | Lines (est.) |\n66: |------|------|--------------|\n67: | `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | Claims and options type definitions | ~80 |\n68: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | JWTValidator implementation | ~150 |\n69: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | HTTP middleware implementation | ~120 |\n70: | `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | Environment-based configuration | ~80 |\n71: | `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | Error type definitions | ~60 |\n72: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | Unit tests for validator | ~200 |\n73: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | Unit tests for middleware | ~150 |\n74: \n75: ### Architecture\n76: \n77: ```\n78: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n79: │                    Client Application                    │\n80: │         (with JWT token from Identity Provider)          │\n81: └─────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────┘\n82:                       │\n83:                       ▼\n84: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n85: │                    HTTP Server                           │\n86: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n87: │  │           JWTMiddleware                          │    │\n88: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────┐  │    │\n89: │  │  │   Extract   │──►│  Validate   │──►│ Verify  │  │    │\n90: │  │  │    Token    │  │   Format    │  │Signature│  │    │\n91: │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └────┬────┘  │    │\n92: │  │                                         │       │    │\n93: │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐      │       │    │\n94: │  │  │   Inject    │◄──│  Validate   │◄─────┘       │    │\n95: │  │  │   Claims    │  │   Claims    │              │    │\n96: │  │  │  to Context │  │ (exp, iss)  │              │    │\n97: │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘              │    │\n98: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n99: │                          │                              │\n100: │                          ▼                              │\n101: │  ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────┐    │\n102: │  │              PicoD API Handler                   │    │\n103: │  │           (AR-015 Command Execution)             │    │\n104: │  └─────────────────────────────────────────────────┘    │\n105: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n106: ```\n107: \n108: ### Middleware Flow\n109: \n110: ```\n111: Incoming Request\n112:        │\n113:        ▼\n114: ┌──────────────┐\n115: │ Extract      │\n116: │ Bearer Token │\n117: │ from Header  │\n118: └──────────────┘\n119:        │\n120:        ├─ Missing ──► Return 401\n121:        │\n122:        ▼\n123: ┌──────────────┐\n124: │ Validate     │\n125: │ Token Format │\n126: └──────────────┘\n127:        │\n128:        ├─ Invalid ──► Return 401\n129:        │\n130:        ▼\n131: ┌──────────────┐\n132: │ Verify       │\n133: │ Signature    │\n134: │ (HS256/RS256)│\n135: └──────────────┘\n136:        │\n137:        ├─ Invalid ──► Return 401\n138:        │\n139:        ▼\n140: ┌──────────────┐\n141: │ Validate     │\n142: │ Claims       │\n143: │ (exp, iss)   │\n144: └──────────────┘\n145:        │\n146:        ├─ Expired ──► Return 401\n147:        ├─ Bad Issuer ► Return 403\n148:        │\n149:        ▼\n150: ┌──────────────┐\n151: │ Call Handler │\n152: │ with Claims  │\n153: │ in Context   │\n154: └──────────────┘\n155: ```\n156: \n157: ### Core Types\n158: \n159: #### JWTValidator Interface\n160: \n161: ```go\n162: type JWTValidator interface {\n163:     // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns the parsed claims\n164:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n165: }\n166: ```\n167: \n168: #### Claims Structure\n169: \n170: ```go\n171: type Claims struct {\n172:     Subject   string    `json:\"sub\"`  // User/subject identifier\n173:     Issuer    string    `json:\"iss\"`  // Token issuer\n174:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`  // Expiration timestamp\n175:     IssuedAt  time.Time `json:\"iat\"`  // Issued-at timestamp\n176: }\n177: ```\n178: \n179: #### ValidationOptions\n180: \n181: ```go\n182: type ValidationOptions struct {\n183:     Algorithm      string           // \"HS256\" or \"RS256\"\n184:     Secret         []byte           // HMAC secret for HS256\n185:     PublicKey      *rsa.PublicKey   // RSA public key for RS256\n186:     ExpectedIssuer string           // Expected issuer claim\n187:     ClockSkew      time.Duration    // Allowed clock skew (default 1m)\n188:     AllowedAlgs    []string         // Allowed algorithms whitelist\n189: }\n190: ```\n191: \n192: #### MiddlewareOptions\n193: \n194: ```go\n195: type MiddlewareOptions struct {\n196:     Validator    JWTValidator\n197:     ErrorHandler func(http.ResponseWriter, error)\n198: }\n199: ```\n200: \n201: #### NewValidator Constructor\n202: \n203: ```go\n204: // NewValidator creates a JWTValidator with the specified options\n205: func NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error)\n206: ```\n207: \n208: #### Middleware Function\n209: \n210: ```go\n211: // JWTMiddleware creates an HTTP middleware for JWT validation\n212: func JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n213: \n214: // GetClaims retrieves validated claims from request context\n215: func GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n216: ```\n217: \n218: ---\n219: \n220: ## Execution Flows\n221: \n222: ### Token Validation (HS256)\n223: \n224: ```\n225: ValidateToken(token)\n226:     │\n227:     ▼\n228: Parse JWT header to extract algorithm\n229:     │\n230:     ▼\n231: Verify algorithm is in AllowedAlgs\n232:     │\n233:     ├─ Unsupported ──► Return ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm\n234:     │\n235:     ▼\n236: Verify algorithm matches configured Algorithm\n237:     │\n238:     ├─ Mismatch ──► Return ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm\n239:     │\n240:     ▼\n241: Parse JWT claims\n242:     │\n243:     ├─ Malformed ──► Return ErrInvalidTokenFormat\n244:     │\n245:     ▼\n246: Verify HMAC signature using configured Secret\n247:     │\n248:     ├─ Invalid ──► Return ErrInvalidSignature\n249:     │\n250:     ▼\n251: Validate exp claim (with ClockSkew tolerance)\n252:     │\n253:     ├─ Expired ──► Return ErrTokenExpired\n254:     │\n255:     ▼\n256: Validate iss claim against ExpectedIssuer\n257:     │\n258:     ├─ Mismatch ──► Return ErrInvalidIssuer\n259:     │\n260:     ▼\n261: Return parsed Claims\n262: ```\n263: \n264: ### Token Validation (RS256)\n265: \n266: ```\n267: ValidateToken(token)\n268:     │\n269:     ▼\n270: Parse JWT header to extract algorithm\n271:     │\n272:     ▼\n273: Verify algorithm is RSA-based and allowed\n274:     │\n275:     ▼\n276: Parse JWT claims\n277:     │\n278:     ▼\n279: Verify RSA signature using configured PublicKey\n280:     │\n281:     ├─ Invalid ──► Return ErrInvalidSignature\n282:     │\n283:     ▼\n284: Validate exp claim (with ClockSkew tolerance)\n285:     │\n286:     ├─ Expired ──► Return ErrTokenExpired\n287:     │\n288:     ▼\n289: Validate iss claim against ExpectedIssuer\n290:     │\n291:     ├─ Mismatch ──► Return ErrInvalidIssuer\n292:     │\n293:     ▼\n294: Return parsed Claims\n295: ```\n296: \n297: ### HTTP Middleware Processing\n298: \n299: ```\n300: JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n301:     │\n302:     ▼\n303: Incoming HTTP request\n304:     │\n305:     ▼\n306: Extract Authorization header\n307:     │\n308:     ├─ Missing ──► Return 401 + JSON error\n309:     │\n310:     ▼\n311: Check Bearer prefix\n312:     │\n313:     ├─ Missing/Invalid ──► Return 401 + JSON error\n314:     │\n315:     ▼\n316: Extract token string\n317:     │\n318:     ▼\n319: Call validator.ValidateToken(token)\n320:     │\n321:     ├─ ErrInvalidSignature ──► Return 401 + JSON error\n322:     ├─ ErrTokenExpired ──────► Return 401 + JSON error\n323:     ├─ ErrInvalidIssuer ─────► Return 403 + JSON error\n324:     ├─ Other errors ─────────► Return 401 + JSON error\n325:     │\n326:     ▼\n327: Add claims to request context\n328:     │\n329:     ▼\n330: Call wrapped handler with enhanced context\n331: ```\n332: \n333: ---\n334: \n335: ## Error Handling\n336: \n337: ### Error Types\n338: \n339: | Error | Code | Description |\n340: |-------|------|-------------|\n341: | `ErrMissingToken` | `MISSING_TOKEN` | No Authorization header present |\n342: | `ErrInvalidTokenFormat` | `INVALID_TOKEN_FORMAT` | Malformed Authorization header or JWT |\n343: | `ErrInvalidSignature` | `INVALID_SIGNATURE` | Signature verification failed |\n344: | `ErrTokenExpired` | `TOKEN_EXPIRED` | Token has expired |\n345: | `ErrInvalidIssuer` | `INVALID_ISSUER` | Issuer claim mismatch |\n346: | `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm` | `UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM` | Algorithm not in allowed list |\n347: \n348: ### HTTP Responses\n349: \n350: | Scenario | Status | Body |\n351: |----------|--------|------|\n352: | Missing token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing bearer token\"}` |\n353: | Invalid format | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token format\"}` |\n354: | Invalid signature | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token signature\"}` |\n355: | Expired token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}` |\n356: | Invalid issuer | 403 | `{\"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"invalid issuer\"}` |\n357: | Unsupported algorithm | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"unsupported algorithm\"}` |\n358: \n359: ---\n360: \n361: ## Security Considerations\n362: \n363: ### Token Transmission\n364: - Tokens MUST be transmitted via HTTPS in production\n365: - HTTP in development only with appropriate warnings\n366: \n367: ### Key Management\n368: - HMAC secrets MUST be securely stored (e.g., Kubernetes secrets)\n369: - RSA public keys should be rotated periodically\n370: - Private keys for token signing are NOT handled by this middleware\n371: \n372: ### Validation Security\n373: - Short token expiration recommended (minutes to hours)\n374: - Clock skew tolerance kept minimal (default 1 minute)\n375: - Algorithm explicitly specified to prevent \"none\" algorithm attacks\n376: - Allowed algorithms whitelist prevents unexpected algorithm usage\n377: \n378: ### Path Security\n379: - Workspace isolation ensures tokens are scoped appropriately\n380: - Claims context propagation follows request lifecycle\n381: \n382: ---\n383: \n384: ## Impact Analysis\n385: \n386: ### Files Created\n387: \n388: | File | Lines (est.) | Description |\n389: |------|--------------|-------------|\n390: | `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | ~80 | Claims and options type definitions |\n391: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | ~150 | JWTValidator implementation |\n392: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | ~120 | HTTP middleware implementation |\n393: | `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | ~80 | Environment-based configuration |\n394: | `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | ~60 | Error type definitions |\n395: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | ~200 | Unit tests for validator |\n396: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | ~150 | Unit tests for middleware |\n397: \n398: ### Dependencies\n399: \n400: ```go\n401: import (\n402:     \"context\"\n403:     \"crypto/rsa\"\n404:     \"errors\"\n405:     \"fmt\"\n406:     \"net/http\"\n407:     \"strings\"\n408:     \"time\"\n409:     \n410:     \"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n411: )\n412: ```\n413: \n414: | Package | Purpose |\n415: |---------|---------|\n416: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT parsing and validation library |\n417: \n418: ### Downstream Consumers\n419: \n420: | Consumer | Usage |\n421: |----------|-------|\n422: | PicoD API Server | Protects command execution endpoints (AR-015) |\n423: | Session Manager | Validates tokens for session operations |\n424: | CLI Tooling | Token-aware request handling |\n425: \n426: ### Performance Characteristics\n427: \n428: | Operation | Complexity | Notes |\n429: |-----------|------------|-------|\n430: | Token parsing | O(1) | Fixed JWT structure parsing |\n431: | HS256 validation | O(1) | Fast HMAC computation |\n432: | RS256 validation | O(1) | Slower RSA signature verification |\n433: | Context propagation | O(1) | Simple pointer passing |\n434: \n435: ### Algorithm Performance Comparison\n436: \n437: | Algorithm | Relative Speed | Use Case |\n438: |-----------|----------------|----------|\n439: | HS256 | Fast (1x) | Internal services, symmetric trust |\n440: | RS256 | Slower (~10x) | External clients, asymmetric trust |\n441: \n442: ---\n443: \n444: ## Alternatives Considered\n445: \n446: ### Alternative 1: Use Standard OAuth2/OIDC Middleware\n447: \n448: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n449: |--------|------------|\n450: | **Pros** | Full standard compliance; broader ecosystem support; automatic token refresh handling |\n451: | **Cons** | Heavy dependency footprint; more complex configuration; unnecessary features for our use case |\n452: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Custom JWT middleware provides sufficient functionality with minimal dependencies |\n453: \n454: ### Alternative 2: Implement Custom JWT Parsing (No Library)\n455: \n456: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n457: |--------|------------|\n458: | **Pros** | Zero external dependencies; full control over implementation; minimal binary size |\n459: | **Cons** | Security risk if implementation flawed; maintenance burden; lacks battle-tested validation |\n460: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — Using established `golang-jwt/jwt` library provides security and reliability |\n461: \n462: ### Alternative 3: API Gateway-Level Authentication\n463: \n464: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n465: |--------|------------|\n466: | **Pros** | Centralized authentication; service doesn't handle auth logic; works with existing gateways |\n467: | **Cons** | Requires gateway deployment; less flexible per-endpoint configuration; claims not available to service |\n468: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — In-middleware approach provides better integration with PicoD context and per-handler flexibility |\n469: \n470: ### Alternative 4: Session-Based Authentication (Cookies)\n471: \n472: | Aspect | Evaluation |\n473: |--------|------------|\n474: | **Pros** | Stateless clients; simpler for browser-based clients; built-in session management |\n475: | **Cons** | Requires session storage; CSRF concerns; less suitable for API-only clients |\n476: | **Decision** | **Rejected** — JWT tokens better fit the stateless API architecture and cross-service authentication needs |\n477: \n478: ---\n479: \n480: ## Risks and Mitigations\n481: \n482: | Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Mitigation |\n483: |------|------------|--------|------------|\n484: | Weak HMAC secrets | Low | Critical | Configuration validation; minimum secret length enforcement; secure secret generation guidance |\n485: | RSA key confusion attacks | Low | High | Explicit algorithm configuration; algorithm whitelist; reject \"none\" algorithm |\n486: | Clock skew causing token rejection | Medium | Medium | Configurable clock skew tolerance; clear documentation on time synchronization |\n487: | Token replay attacks | Low | Medium | Short token expiration; consider token binding in future |\n488: | Algorithm confusion attacks | Low | Critical | Strict algorithm validation; separate code paths for HS256/RS256 |\n489: | Key extraction from memory | Low | High | Use secure string handling; minimize key exposure time |\n490: | JWT library vulnerabilities | Low | Critical | Use well-maintained library; regular dependency updates; CVE monitoring |\n491: | Configuration errors on startup | Medium | High | Fail-fast validation; clear error messages; configuration documentation |\n492: \n493: ---\n494: \n495: ## Verification\n496: \n497: ### Unit Tests\n498: \n499: ```bash\n500: # Run all JWT middleware tests\n501: make test PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n502: \n503: # Run with race detector\n504: go test -race ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n505: \n506: # Run specific test categories\n507: go test -v ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -run \"TestValidateToken\"\n508: go test -v ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -run \"TestMiddleware\"\n509: ```\n510: \n511: ### Integration Tests\n512: \n513: ```bash\n514: # Run integration tests\n515: make integration-test PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n516: \n517: # With coverage\n518: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n519: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n520: ```\n521: \n522: ### Manual Verification\n523: \n524: ```bash\n525: # Build verification\n526: go build ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n527: \n528: # Interface compliance check\n529: go build ./...\n530: \n531: # Lint check\n532: make lint PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n533: ```\n534: \n535: ### Test Scenarios\n536: \n537: | Scenario | Expected Result |\n538: |----------|-----------------|\n539: | Valid HS256 token | Returns parsed Claims with no error |\n540: | Valid RS256 token | Returns parsed Claims with no error |\n541: | Invalid HS256 signature | Returns ErrInvalidSignature |\n542: | Invalid RS256 signature | Returns ErrInvalidSignature |\n543: | Expired token | Returns ErrTokenExpired |\n544: | Token with clock skew within tolerance | Returns parsed Claims |\n545: | Wrong issuer | Returns ErrInvalidIssuer |\n546: | Unsupported algorithm | Returns ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm |\n547: | Request with valid token (middleware) | Proceeds to handler with claims in context |\n548: | Request without token (middleware) | Returns 401 with JSON error |\n549: | Request with invalid format (middleware) | Returns 401 with JSON error |\n550: | Request with expired token (middleware) | Returns 401 with JSON error |\n551: | Request with wrong issuer (middleware) | Returns 403 with JSON error |\n552: | Configuration loading from environment | Correctly parses all settings |\n553: | Missing required configuration | Returns error on startup |\n554: \n555: ---\n556: \n557: ## References\n558: \n559: - [PicoD JWT Design](changes/AR-017/design.md) — Detailed design document\n560: - [PicoD JWT Delta Spec](changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md) — API specification changes\n561: - [PicoD JWT Tests](changes/AR-017/tests.md) — Test specifications\n562: - [PicoD JWT Plan](changes/AR-017/plan.md) — Implementation plan\n563: - [AR-015 Command Execution](changes/AR-015/design.md) — Base API that this middleware protects\n564: - [client-go Library](deployment/client-go.md) — Kubernetes client patterns for agentcube\n565: \n566: ---\n567: \n568: ## Success Criteria\n569: \n570: 1. ✅ JWTValidator interface fully implemented with HS256 and RS256 support\n571: 2. ✅ Token validation correctly verifies signatures for both algorithms\n572: 3. ✅ Claims validation (exp, iss, iat) with configurable clock skew\n573: 4. ✅ HTTP middleware extracts and validates Bearer tokens\n574: 5. ✅ Context propagation allows handlers to access parsed claims\n575: 6. ✅ Environment-based configuration with validation\n576: 7. ✅ Standardized HTTP 401/403 error responses\n577: 8. ✅ Unit test coverage >= 85%\n578: 9. ✅ Integration tests passing\n579: 10. ✅ Race detector shows no issues\n580: 11. ✅ Documentation complete with usage examples\n581: \n582: ---\n583: \n584: *AR-017 — Module: pkg/picod/jwt — Language: Go — Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 584 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Proposal: PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## AR-017 — PicoD JWT 中间件\n\n| Field | Value |\n|-------|-------|\n| **Module** | `pkg/picod/jwt` |\n| **Language** | Go |\n| **Size** | S (Small) |\n| **Status** | Proposed |\n\n---\n\n## Purpose\n\nImplement the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer that provides secure token-based authentication for agentcube platform endpoints. This proposal delivers:\n\n1. **Token Validation**: Support for HS256 (HMAC-SHA256) and RS256 (RSA-SHA256) JWT signature verification\n2. **Claims Validation**: Verification of standard claims including expiration (`exp`), issuer (`iss`), and issued-at (`iat`) with configurable clock skew tolerance\n3. **HTTP Middleware**: Injectable middleware for HTTP handlers that extracts and validates Bearer tokens from Authorization headers","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/proposal.md","time":{"start":1775877934862,"end":1775877934890}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877934902,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a92bc040014BglaKL2be28H5","messageID":"msg_d7a9290250017FrAY3CuGOfCM4","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the architecture and design of the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer in the agentcube platform.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n14: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n15: │  HTTP Handler ──────► JWT Middleware ──────► Handler    │\n16: │                           │                              │\n17: │                           ▼                              │\n18: │                   Token Validation                       │\n19: │                   (Signature + Claims)                   │\n20: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Middleware Flow\n24: \n25: ```\n26: Incoming Request\n27:        │\n28:        ▼\n29: ┌──────────────┐\n30: │ Extract      │\n31: │ Bearer Token │\n32: └──────────────┘\n33:        │\n34:        ▼\n35: ┌──────────────┐\n36: │ Validate     │\n37: │ Token Format │\n38: └──────────────┘\n39:        │\n40:        ▼\n41: ┌──────────────┐\n42: │ Verify       │\n43: │ Signature    │\n44: └──────────────┘\n45:        │\n46:        ▼\n47: ┌──────────────┐\n48: │ Validate     │\n49: │ Claims       │\n50: │ (exp, iss)   │\n51: └──────────────┘\n52:        │\n53:        ▼\n54:    [Valid] ────► Call Handler\n55:        │\n56:    [Invalid] ──► Return 401/403\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ## Key Interfaces\n60: \n61: ### JWTValidator\n62: \n63: Core interface for token validation.\n64: \n65: ```go\n66: type JWTValidator interface {\n67:     // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns the parsed claims\n68:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### Middleware Function\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: // Middleware wraps an HTTP handler with JWT validation\n76: func JWTMiddleware(validator JWTValidator, opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Claims Structure\n80: \n81: ```go\n82: type Claims struct {\n83:     Subject   string    `json:\"sub\"`\n84:     Issuer    string    `json:\"iss\"`\n85:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`\n86:     IssuedAt  time.Time `json:\"iat\"`\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### Validation Options\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: type ValidationOptions struct {\n94:     Issuer        string        // Expected issuer claim\n95:     ClockSkew     time.Duration // Allowed clock skew for exp validation\n96:     AllowedAlgs   []string      // Allowed signing algorithms\n97: }\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ## Supported Algorithms\n101: \n102: | Algorithm | Type | Key Format |\n103: |-----------|------|------------|\n104: | HS256 | HMAC-SHA256 | []byte (symmetric) |\n105: | RS256 | RSA-SHA256 | *rsa.PublicKey |\n106: \n107: ## Configuration\n108: \n109: ### Environment Variables\n110: \n111: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n112: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n113: | `PICOD_JWT_SECRET` | HS256 only | - | HMAC secret for HS256 |\n114: | `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY` | RS256 only | - | Path to RSA public key file |\n115: | `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER` | Yes | - | Expected issuer claim |\n116: | `PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW` | No | 1m | Clock skew tolerance |\n117: | `PICOD_JWT_ALG` | No | RS256 | Signing algorithm |\n118: \n119: ## Error Handling\n120: \n121: ### Error Types\n122: \n123: - `ErrMissingToken`: No Authorization header present\n124: - `ErrInvalidTokenFormat`: Malformed Authorization header\n125: - `ErrInvalidSignature`: Signature verification failed\n126: - `ErrTokenExpired`: Token has expired\n127: - `ErrInvalidIssuer`: Issuer claim mismatch\n128: - `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm`: Algorithm not in allowed list\n129: \n130: ### HTTP Responses\n131: \n132: | Scenario | Status | Body |\n133: |----------|--------|------|\n134: | Missing token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing bearer token\"}` |\n135: | Invalid signature | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token signature\"}` |\n136: | Expired token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}` |\n137: | Invalid issuer | 403 | `{\"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"invalid issuer\"}` |\n138: \n139: ## Security Considerations\n140: \n141: - Tokens must be transmitted via HTTPS\n142: - HMAC secrets must be securely stored\n143: - RSA public keys should be rotated periodically\n144: - Short token expiration recommended\n145: - Clock skew tolerance kept minimal\n146: \n147: ## Performance Considerations\n148: \n149: - RSA signature verification is slower than HMAC\n150: - Consider caching parsed keys\n151: - Minimize allocations in hot path\n152: - Early rejection for missing headers\n153: \n154: ## Open Questions\n155: \n156: 1. Should we support JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) for key rotation?\n157: 2. Do we need audience claim validation?\n158: 3. Should we support multiple issuers?\n159: 4. Is token binding to specific endpoints required?\n\n(End of file - total 159 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the architecture and design of the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer in the agentcube platform.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  HTTP Handler ──────► JWT Middleware ──────► Handler    │\n│                           │                              │\n│                           ▼                              │\n│                   Token Validation                       │\n│                   (Signature + Claims)                   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md","time":{"start":1775877934857,"end":1775877934900}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877934904,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a92c29a001Ik0GTNoM24A9Uy","messageID":"msg_d7a9290250017FrAY3CuGOfCM4","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/spec.yaml"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/spec.yaml</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: id: AR-017\n2: title: PicoD JWT 中间件\n3: module: pkg/picod\n4: language: Go\n5: size: S\n6: status: open\n7: \n8: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件\n9: # Module: pkg/picod\n10: # Language: Go\n11: # Size: S\n12: \n13: # OpenSpec Metadata\n14: openspec:\n15:   version: \"1.0\"\n16:   project: agentcube\n17: \n18: # Architecture Requirement\n19: requirement:\n20:   type: picod-jwt-middleware\n21:   description: |\n22:     Implement JWT (JSON Web Token) authentication middleware for PicoD that\n23:     validates bearer tokens on incoming API requests. The middleware provides\n24:     secure access control to PicoD command execution endpoints by verifying\n25:     token signatures, expiration, and issuer claims.\n26: \n27: # Scope\n28: scope:\n29:   in:\n30:     - JWT middleware for HTTP/gRPC request validation\n31:     - Token signature verification (HS256, RS256 algorithms)\n32:     - Token expiration and issuer claim validation\n33:     - Middleware injection into PicoD API handlers\n34:     - Configuration for JWT keys and validation rules\n35:     - Error handling for invalid/missing tokens\n36:   out:\n37:     - Full OAuth2/OIDC flow implementation\n38:     - Token refresh mechanism\n39:     - Authorization scope enforcement (RBAC)\n40:     - Session management\n41:     - Token generation/issuance\n42: \n43: # Acceptance Criteria\n44: acceptance:\n45:   - JWT middleware validates bearer tokens on requests\n46:   - Support for HS256 and RS256 signing algorithms\n47:   - Token expiration validation with configurable clock skew\n48:   - Issuer claim validation\n49:   - Proper error responses for authentication failures\n50:   - Middleware can be applied to specific routes/endpoints\n51:   - Configuration via environment variables\n52:   - Unit tests for validation logic\n53:   - Integration tests with mock JWT provider\n54: \n55: # References\n56: references:\n57:   - AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API\n58:   - RFC 7519: JSON Web Token (JWT)\n59: \n60: # Estimation\n61: estimation:\n62:   size: S\n63:   story_points: 2\n64:   days: 2\n\n(End of file - total 64 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"id: AR-017\ntitle: PicoD JWT 中间件\nmodule: pkg/picod\nlanguage: Go\nsize: S\nstatus: open\n\n# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件\n# Module: pkg/picod\n# Language: Go\n# Size: S\n\n# OpenSpec Metadata\nopenspec:\n  version: \"1.0\"\n  project: agentcube\n\n# Architecture Requirement\nrequirement:\n  type: picod-jwt-middleware","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/spec.yaml","time":{"start":1775877934860,"end":1775877934902}}}}
