{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877957187,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a9318a10017jyP46DMQ3aF2X","messageID":"msg_d7a92cf74001pXG5ANDlgmu5Tx","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:7","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Delta Specification\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-017  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S  \n9: **Base Spec:** AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API)\n10: \n11: The PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms.\n12: \n13: ---\n14: \n15: ## Requirements\n16: \n17: ### Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n18: \n19: The system SHALL validate JWT tokens from the Authorization header using configurable signing algorithms and claims.\n20: \n21: #### Scenario: Valid HS256 token passes validation\n22: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with HS256 and secret \"test-secret\"\n23: - **AND** `ValidationOptions{Algorithm: \"HS256\", Secret: []byte(\"test-secret\")}`\n24: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n25: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL verify the HMAC signature\n26: - **AND** return parsed `Claims` with no error\n27: \n28: #### Scenario: Valid RS256 token passes validation\n29: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with RS256 using a private key\n30: - **AND** the corresponding public key is configured\n31: - **AND** `ValidationOptions{Algorithm: \"RS256\", PublicKey: rsaPubKey}`\n32: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n33: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL verify the RSA signature\n34: - **AND** return parsed `Claims` with no error\n35: \n36: #### Scenario: Invalid signature returns error\n37: - **GIVEN** a JWT token with invalid signature\n38: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n39: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrInvalidSignature`\n40: \n41: #### Scenario: Expired token returns error\n42: - **GIVEN** a JWT token with `exp` claim in the past\n43: - **AND** no clock skew configured\n44: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n45: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrTokenExpired`\n46: \n47: #### Scenario: Clock skew allows near-expired tokens\n48: - **GIVEN** a JWT token expired 30 seconds ago\n49: - **AND** `ClockSkew: 1m` configured\n50: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n51: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL accept the token\n52: - **AND** return parsed `Claims` with no error\n53: \n54: #### Scenario: Wrong issuer returns error\n55: - **GIVEN** a JWT token with `iss: \"other-service\"`\n56: - **AND** `ExpectedIssuer: \"auth-service\"` configured\n57: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n58: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrInvalidIssuer`\n59: \n60: #### Scenario: Unsupported algorithm returns error\n61: - **GIVEN** a JWT token signed with ES256\n62: - **AND** `AllowedAlgorithms: [\"HS256\", \"RS256\"]` configured\n63: - **WHEN** `ValidateToken(token)` is called\n64: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm`\n65: \n66: ---\n67: \n68: ### Requirement: HTTP Middleware\n69: \n70: The system SHALL provide HTTP middleware that extracts and validates JWT tokens from requests.\n71: \n72: #### Scenario: Request with valid token proceeds to handler\n73: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with `Authorization: Bearer <valid_token>`\n74: - **AND** JWTMiddleware is configured with valid validator\n75: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n76: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL extract the token\n77: - **AND** validate it successfully\n78: - **AND** call the wrapped handler\n79: \n80: #### Scenario: Request without token returns 401\n81: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request without Authorization header\n82: - **WHEN** the request is processed by JWTMiddleware\n83: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n84: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing bearer token\"}`\n85: \n86: #### Scenario: Request with invalid token format returns 401\n87: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with `Authorization: invalid_format`\n88: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n89: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n90: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token format\"}`\n91: \n92: #### Scenario: Invalid signature returns 401\n93: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with `Authorization: Bearer <bad_sig_token>`\n94: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n95: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n96: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token signature\"}`\n97: \n98: #### Scenario: Expired token returns 401\n99: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with expired JWT token\n100: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n101: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 401\n102: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}`\n103: \n104: #### Scenario: Invalid issuer returns 403\n105: - **GIVEN** an HTTP request with token from wrong issuer\n106: - **WHEN** the request is processed\n107: - **THEN** the middleware SHALL return HTTP 403\n108: - **AND** body SHALL be `{\"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"invalid issuer\"}`\n109: \n110: #### Scenario: Claims are added to request context\n111: - **GIVEN** a valid JWT token with claims\n112: - **AND** a request with `Authorization: Bearer <token>`\n113: - **WHEN** the wrapped handler is called\n114: - **THEN** the request context SHALL contain the parsed `Claims`\n115: - **AND** the handler can retrieve claims via `GetClaims(ctx)`\n116: \n117: ---\n118: \n119: ### Requirement: Configuration\n120: \n121: The system SHALL support configuration via environment variables.\n122: \n123: #### Scenario: HS256 configuration loads secret from env\n124: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_JWT_SECRET=my-secret`\n125: - **AND** `PICOD_JWT_ALG=HS256`\n126: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n127: - **THEN** the validator SHALL use HMAC with secret \"my-secret\"\n128: \n129: #### Scenario: RS256 configuration loads public key from file\n130: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY=/path/to/key.pem`\n131: - **AND** `PICOD_JWT_ALG=RS256`\n132: - **AND** a valid RSA public key file at that path\n133: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n134: - **THEN** the validator SHALL use the loaded RSA public key\n135: \n136: #### Scenario: Issuer is required configuration\n137: - **GIVEN** no `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER` environment variable\n138: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n139: - **THEN** the implementation SHALL return an error\n140: - **AND** fail fast on startup\n141: \n142: #### Scenario: Clock skew configuration is parsed\n143: - **GIVEN** environment `PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW=2m`\n144: - **WHEN** configuration is loaded\n145: - **THEN** the validator SHALL allow 2 minutes of clock skew\n146: \n147: ---\n148: \n149: ## Changes to Base Specification\n150: \n151: This AR adds authentication middleware to AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API). No modifications to existing interfaces.\n152: \n153: ---\n154: \n155: ## New Interfaces\n156: \n157: ### JWTValidator Interface\n158: \n159: ```go\n160: package jwt\n161: \n162: import \"context\"\n163: \n164: // JWTValidator validates JWT tokens\n165: type JWTValidator interface {\n166:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n167: }\n168: \n169: // Claims represents validated JWT claims\n170: type Claims struct {\n171:     Subject   string    `json:\"sub\"`\n172:     Issuer    string    `json:\"iss\"`\n173:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`\n174:     IssuedAt  time.Time `json:\"iat\"`\n175: }\n176: \n177: // ValidationOptions configures the validator\n178: type ValidationOptions struct {\n179:     Algorithm       string\n180:     Secret          []byte        // For HS256\n181:     PublicKey       *rsa.PublicKey // For RS256\n182:     ExpectedIssuer  string\n183:     ClockSkew       time.Duration\n184:     AllowedAlgs     []string\n185: }\n186: \n187: // NewValidator creates a JWTValidator with options\n188: func NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error)\n189: ```\n190: \n191: ### Middleware Function\n192: \n193: ```go\n194: // MiddlewareOptions configures the middleware behavior\n195: type MiddlewareOptions struct {\n196:     Validator    JWTValidator\n197:     ErrorHandler func(http.ResponseWriter, error)\n198: }\n199: \n200: // JWTMiddleware creates an HTTP middleware for JWT validation\n201: func JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n202: \n203: // GetClaims retrieves validated claims from context\n204: func GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n205: ```\n206: \n207: ### Error Types\n208: \n209: ```go\n210: var (\n211:     ErrMissingToken         = errors.New(\"jwt: missing bearer token\")\n212:     ErrInvalidTokenFormat   = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid token format\")\n213:     ErrInvalidSignature     = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid signature\")\n214:     ErrTokenExpired         = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n215:     ErrInvalidIssuer        = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid issuer\")\n216:     ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm = errors.New(\"jwt: unsupported algorithm\")\n217: )\n218: ```\n219: \n220: ---\n221: \n222: ## Modified Interfaces\n223: \n224: None. This AR introduces new functionality without modifying existing interfaces.\n225: \n226: ---\n227: \n228: ## Behavioral Changes\n229: \n230: | Behavior | Before | After |\n231: |----------|--------|-------|\n232: | API authentication | None | JWT token validation required |\n233: | Request processing | Direct | Through middleware layer |\n234: | Error responses | Application-defined | Standardized auth errors |\n235: \n236: ---\n237: \n238: ## Dependencies\n239: \n240: | Dependency | Version | Purpose |\n241: |------------|---------|---------|\n242: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | v5.x | JWT parsing and validation |\n243: | `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/picod` | Local | Integration with AR-015 |\n244: \n245: ---\n246: \n247: ## File Index\n248: \n249: | Path | Purpose |\n250: |------|---------|\n251: | `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | Claims and options types |\n252: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | JWTValidator implementation |\n253: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | HTTP middleware |\n254: | `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | Configuration loading |\n255: | `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | Error definitions |\n256: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | Unit tests |\n257: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | Middleware tests |\n258: \n259: ---\n260: \n261: ## Constants\n262: \n263: | Constant | Value | Description |\n264: |----------|-------|-------------|\n265: | `defaultClockSkew` | `1m` | Default clock skew tolerance |\n266: | `authorizationHeader` | `\"Authorization\"` | HTTP header name |\n267: | `bearerPrefix` | `\"Bearer \"` | Token prefix |\n268: \n269: ---\n270: \n271: ## Configuration\n272: \n273: ### Environment Variables\n274: \n275: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n276: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n277: | `PICOD_JWT_SECRET` | HS256 | - | HMAC secret for HS256 |\n278: | `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY` | RS256 | - | Path to RSA public key PEM file |\n279: | `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER` | Yes | - | Expected issuer claim |\n280: | `PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW` | No | `1m` | Clock skew tolerance |\n281: | `PICOD_JWT_ALG` | No | `RS256` | Signing algorithm |\n282: \n283: ---\n284: \n285: ## API Endpoints Summary\n286: \n287: This AR provides middleware functionality; no new endpoints are exposed.\n288: \n289: ---\n290: \n291: ## Migration Notes\n292: \n293: - Add `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` dependency to go.mod\n294: - Configure JWT environment variables before deployment\n295: - Apply middleware to protected routes using `JWTMiddleware(opts)`\n296: - Existing unauthenticated endpoints remain unaffected\n297: \n298: ---\n299: \n300: ## Acceptance Criteria Summary\n301: \n302: 1. **Token Validation**: HS256 and RS256 tokens validated correctly\n303: 2. **Claims Validation**: exp, iss claims validated with clock skew support\n304: 3. **Middleware**: HTTP middleware extracts and validates bearer tokens\n305: 4. **Error Responses**: Appropriate HTTP 401/403 responses for auth failures\n306: 5. **Configuration**: All settings configurable via environment variables\n307: 6. **Context Integration**: Parsed claims available via GetClaims(ctx)\n308: 7. **Unit Tests**: >85% coverage on validation logic\n309: 8. **Integration Tests**: End-to-end middleware flow tested\n\n(End of file - total 309 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Delta Specification\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S  \n**Base Spec:** AR-015 (PicoD 命令执行 API)\n\nThe PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms.\n\n---\n\n## Requirements\n\n### Requirement: JWT Token Validation\n\nThe system SHALL validate JWT tokens from the Authorization header using configurable signing algorithms and claims.\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md","time":{"start":1775877957169,"end":1775877957185}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877957188,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a931cd1001h40rxjt67z0E3W","messageID":"msg_d7a92cf74001pXG5ANDlgmu5Tx","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tests.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tests.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Test Specification\n2: \n3: ## Test Categories\n4: \n5: ### Unit Tests\n6: \n7: #### validator_test.go\n8: \n9: ```go\n10: // TestValidateToken_HS256_Success - Valid HS256 token\n11: // TestValidateToken_HS256_InvalidSignature - Wrong HMAC secret\n12: // TestValidateToken_RS256_Success - Valid RS256 token\n13: // TestValidateToken_RS256_InvalidSignature - Wrong RSA key\n14: // TestValidateToken_Expired - Expired token\n15: // TestValidateToken_NotYetValid - Token used before iat\n16: // TestValidateToken_InvalidIssuer - Issuer mismatch\n17: // TestValidateToken_UnsupportedAlgorithm - Algorithm not allowed\n18: // TestValidateToken_Malformed - Invalid JWT format\n19: // TestValidateToken_MissingClaims - Required claims missing\n20: ```\n21: \n22: #### middleware_test.go\n23: \n24: ```go\n25: // TestMiddleware_ValidToken - Request with valid token passes\n26: // TestMiddleware_MissingToken - Request without token returns 401\n27: // TestMiddleware_InvalidFormat - Malformed Authorization header\n28: // TestMiddleware_ExpiredToken - Expired token returns 401\n29: // TestMiddleware_InvalidIssuer - Wrong issuer returns 403\n30: // TestMiddleware_ValidationError - Other validation errors\n31: // TestMiddleware_ContextPropagation - Claims added to context\n32: ```\n33: \n34: ### Integration Tests\n35: \n36: ```go\n37: // TestIntegration_EndToEnd - Full middleware flow\n38: // TestIntegration_RealToken - Test with actual JWT library\n39: ```\n40: \n41: ### Test Data\n42: \n43: #### Sample HS256 Token\n44: \n45: ```go\n46: // Secret: \"test-secret-12345\"\n47: // Claims: {\"sub\": \"user123\", \"iss\": \"auth-service\", \"exp\": <future>}\n48: ```\n49: \n50: #### Sample RS256 Token\n51: \n52: ```go\n53: // Generated with test RSA key pair\n54: // Claims: {\"sub\": \"user456\", \"iss\": \"auth-service\", \"exp\": <future>}\n55: ```\n56: \n57: #### Expired Token\n58: \n59: ```go\n60: // Claims: {\"sub\": \"user789\", \"iss\": \"auth-service\", \"exp\": <past>}\n61: ```\n62: \n63: ## Coverage Targets\n64: \n65: - Line coverage: >= 85%\n66: - Branch coverage: >= 80%\n67: - Critical paths: 100%\n68: \n69: ## Test Environment\n70: \n71: - Go 1.21+\n72: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` for test token generation\n73: - Mock HTTP handlers for middleware testing\n74: \n75: ## Test Execution\n76: \n77: ```bash\n78: # Unit tests only\n79: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -short\n80: \n81: # All tests including integration\n82: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n83: \n84: # With coverage\n85: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n86: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n87: ```\n\n(End of file - total 87 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Test Specification\n\n## Test Categories\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### validator_test.go\n\n```go\n// TestValidateToken_HS256_Success - Valid HS256 token\n// TestValidateToken_HS256_InvalidSignature - Wrong HMAC secret\n// TestValidateToken_RS256_Success - Valid RS256 token\n// TestValidateToken_RS256_InvalidSignature - Wrong RSA key\n// TestValidateToken_Expired - Expired token\n// TestValidateToken_NotYetValid - Token used before iat\n// TestValidateToken_InvalidIssuer - Issuer mismatch\n// TestValidateToken_UnsupportedAlgorithm - Algorithm not allowed\n// TestValidateToken_Malformed - Invalid JWT format\n// TestValidateToken_MissingClaims - Required claims missing\n```","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/tests.md","time":{"start":1775877957172,"end":1775877957187}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775877957192,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a932149001B8yiWghhBU8hE1","messageID":"msg_d7a92cf74001pXG5ANDlgmu5Tx","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:9","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/plan.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/plan.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Implementation Plan\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: This plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD JWT authentication middleware.\n6: \n7: ## Phase 1: Core Types and Interfaces\n8: \n9: - [ ] Define JWTValidator interface\n10: - [ ] Define Claims struct with standard JWT claims\n11: - [ ] Define ValidationOptions struct\n12: - [ ] Define MiddlewareOptions struct\n13: - [ ] Define error types for validation failures\n14: \n15: ## Phase 2: Token Validation\n16: \n17: - [ ] Implement HS256 signature verification\n18: - [ ] Implement RS256 signature verification\n19: - [ ] Implement token parsing and claims extraction\n20: - [ ] Implement expiration validation with clock skew\n21: - [ ] Implement issuer claim validation\n22: - [ ] Implement algorithm validation\n23: \n24: ## Phase 3: HTTP Middleware\n25: \n26: - [ ] Implement JWTMiddleware function\n27: - [ ] Implement bearer token extraction from Authorization header\n28: - [ ] Implement error handling and HTTP response generation\n29: - [ ] Support configurable middleware options\n30: \n31: ## Phase 4: Configuration\n32: \n33: - [ ] Implement configuration from environment variables\n34: - [ ] Support HMAC secret loading\n35: - [ ] Support RSA public key loading from file\n36: - [ ] Validate configuration on startup\n37: \n38: ## Phase 5: Integration\n39: \n40: - [ ] Create middleware factory for PicoD API\n41: - [ ] Document integration points with AR-015\n42: - [ ] Provide examples of applying middleware to routes\n43: \n44: ## Phase 6: Testing\n45: \n46: - [ ] Write unit tests for token validation\n47: - [ ] Write unit tests for middleware\n48: - [ ] Write integration tests\n49: - [ ] Test with real JWT tokens\n50: \n51: ## Estimated Timeline\n52: \n53: - Phase 1: 0.5 day\n54: - Phase 2: 0.75 day\n55: - Phase 3: 0.5 day\n56: - Phase 4: 0.25 day\n57: - Phase 5: 0.25 day\n58: - Phase 6: 0.5 day\n59: \n60: Total: 2-2.5 days\n61: \n62: ## Dependencies\n63: \n64: - AR-015: PicoD 命令执行 API (for integration)\n65: - `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` or similar JWT library\n66: \n67: ## File Deliverables\n68: \n69: | Path | Purpose |\n70: |------|---------|\n71: | `pkg/picod/jwt/types.go` | Claims and options types |\n72: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator.go` | JWTValidator implementation |\n73: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware.go` | HTTP middleware |\n74: | `pkg/picod/jwt/config.go` | Configuration loading |\n75: | `pkg/picod/jwt/errors.go` | Error definitions |\n76: | `pkg/picod/jwt/validator_test.go` | Unit tests |\n77: | `pkg/picod/jwt/middleware_test.go` | Middleware tests |\n\n(End of file - total 77 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Implementation Plan\n\n## Overview\n\nThis plan outlines the implementation steps for the PicoD JWT authentication middleware.\n\n## Phase 1: Core Types and Interfaces\n\n- [ ] Define JWTValidator interface\n- [ ] Define Claims struct with standard JWT claims\n- [ ] Define ValidationOptions struct\n- [ ] Define MiddlewareOptions struct\n- [ ] Define error types for validation failures\n\n## Phase 2: Token Validation\n\n- [ ] Implement HS256 signature verification\n- [ ] Implement RS256 signature verification\n- [ ] Implement token parsing and claims extraction\n- [ ] Implement expiration validation with clock skew","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/plan.md","time":{"start":1775877957174,"end":1775877957189}}}}
