{"type":"text","timestamp":1775877975737,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a936af30012swGlDrndl8rex","messageID":"msg_d7a934227001WP4LVEPyKCiWvr","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"text","text":"Now I have a comprehensive understanding of the project. I'll write the design.md file for AR-017 (PicoD JWT Middleware) following the detailed technical format similar to AR-016.","time":{"start":1775877975734,"end":1775877975734}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775878249825,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a94312a001GCQNkfiODl1acv","messageID":"msg_d7a934227001WP4LVEPyKCiWvr","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"text","text":" the","time":{"start":1775878249821,"end":1775878249821}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878250600,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a936eb8001L3Rray45gmtdXu","messageID":"msg_d7a934227001WP4LVEPyKCiWvr","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:12","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","content":"# AR-017 Design: PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S (Small)\n\nThe PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms, validates standard claims (expiration, issuer), and integrates with the HTTP middleware chain to protect PicoD command execution endpoints (AR-015).\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **PicoD Command Execution (AR-015)**: Provides authentication layer for command execution endpoints\n- **Router JWT (existing)**: Uses consistent JWT patterns with the router package\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Client Application                                   │\n│                    (with JWT from Identity Provider)                         │\n└─────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────┘\n                                  │\n                                  ▼\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         HTTP Server Layer                                    │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                     JWTMiddleware                                       │  │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌───────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │   Extract   │──►│   Parse     │──►│   Verify    │──►│ Validate  │  │  │\n│  │  │    Token    │   │   Header    │   │  Signature  │   │  Claims   │  │  │\n│  │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────┬─────┘  │  │\n│  │                                                              │        │  │\n│  │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘        │  │\n│  │  │                                                                   │  │\n│  │  ▼                                                                   │  │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐                │  │\n│  │  │    Inject   │──►│    Call     │──►│   Handler   │                │  │\n│  │  │   Claims    │   │   Handler   │   │  Response   │                │  │\n│  │  │  to Context │   │             │   │             │                │  │\n│  │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘                │  │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                      JWT Validation Layer                                    │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │  Token Parser    │  │  Signature Verif │  │  Claims Validator        │   │\n│  │  · Header parse  │  │  · HS256 (HMAC)  │  │  · Expiration (exp)      │   │\n│  │  · Claims decode │  │  · RS256 (RSA)   │  │  · Issuer (iss)          │   │\n│  │  · Algorithm id  │  │  · Key loading   │  │  · Clock skew tolerance  │   │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                      Configuration Layer                                     │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │  Environment     │  │  Secret Loader   │  │  Key Parser              │   │\n│  │  · PICOD_JWT_*   │  │  · HMAC secret   │  │  · PEM decoding          │   │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                       Token Validation Flow                                  │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  Token   │──►│  Parse   │──►│ Validate │──►│  Verify  │──►│ Validate │  │\n│  │  Input   │   │  Header  │   │ Algorithm│   │ Signature│   │  Claims  │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘   └────┬─────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n│                                     │              │              │        │\n│                         ┌───────────┘              │              │        │\n│                         │     ┌────────────────────┘              │        │\n│                         ▼     ▼                                   ▼        │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  Return  │◀──│  Return  │◀──│  Return  │◀──│  Return  │◀──│  Return  │  │\n│  │  Claims  │   │   Err    │   │   Err    │   │   Err    │   │  Claims  │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n│                                                                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n| Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n|-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n| **JWTValidator** | Core interface for token validation | JWT string, ValidationOptions | Parsed Claims or validation error |\n| **TokenParser** | Parses JWT header and claims | Raw JWT string | Parsed header and claims |\n| **SignatureVerifier** | Verifies token signatures | Token, key material | Verification status |\n| **ClaimsValidator** | Validates standard claims | Parsed claims | Validated claims or error |\n| **JWTMiddleware** | HTTP middleware wrapper | HTTP request, handler | Authenticated request or HTTP error |\n| **ConfigLoader** | Loads environment configuration | Environment variables | ValidationOptions |\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\npkg/picod/jwt/\n├── types.go              # Claims and options type definitions (~80 lines)\n├── validator.go          # JWTValidator implementation (~150 lines)\n├── middleware.go         # HTTP middleware implementation (~120 lines)\n├── config.go             # Environment-based configuration (~80 lines)\n├── errors.go             # Error type definitions (~60 lines)\n├── validator_test.go     # Unit tests for validator (~200 lines)\n└── middleware_test.go    # Unit tests for middleware (~150 lines)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Request/Response Types\n\n#### Claims\n\n```go\n// Claims represents validated JWT claims extracted from a token.\n// These claims are propagated to downstream handlers via context.\ntype Claims struct {\n    // Subject is the user/subject identifier\n    Subject string `json:\"sub\"`\n\n    // Issuer identifies the principal that issued the JWT\n    Issuer string `json:\"iss\"`\n\n    // ExpiresAt is the expiration time on or after which the token MUST NOT be accepted\n    ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`\n\n    // IssuedAt is the time at which the JWT was issued\n    IssuedAt time.Time `json:\"iat\"`\n}\n\n// IsExpired checks if the token is expired considering clock skew.\nfunc (c *Claims) IsExpired(clockSkew time.Duration) bool {\n    return time.Now().After(c.ExpiresAt.Add(clockSkew))\n}\n\n// IsValidIssuer checks if the issuer matches the expected value.\nfunc (c *Claims) IsValidIssuer(expected string) bool {\n    return c.Issuer == expected\n}\n```\n\n#### ValidationOptions\n\n```go\n// ValidationOptions configures the JWT validator behavior.\ntype ValidationOptions struct {\n    // Algorithm is the expected signing algorithm (\"HS256\" or \"RS256\")\n    Algorithm string\n\n    // Secret is the HMAC secret for HS256 validation\n    Secret []byte\n\n    // PublicKey is the RSA public key for RS256 validation\n    PublicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n\n    // ExpectedIssuer is the required issuer claim value\n    ExpectedIssuer string\n\n    // ClockSkew is the allowed time difference for exp validation\n    ClockSkew time.Duration\n\n    // AllowedAlgs is the whitelist of allowed signing algorithms\n    AllowedAlgs []string\n}\n\n// DefaultValidationOptions returns default options with safe defaults.\nfunc DefaultValidationOptions() ValidationOptions {\n    return ValidationOptions{\n        Algorithm:   \"RS256\",\n        ClockSkew:   time.Minute,\n        AllowedAlgs: []string{\"HS256\", \"RS256\"},\n    }\n}\n\n// Validate checks if the options are valid for use.\nfunc (o *ValidationOptions) Validate() error {\n    if o.ExpectedIssuer == \"\" {\n        return ErrInvalidConfig\n    }\n    if o.Algorithm == \"\" {\n        return ErrInvalidConfig\n    }\n    if o.Algorithm == \"HS256\" && len(o.Secret) == 0 {\n        return ErrInvalidConfig\n    }\n    if o.Algorithm == \"RS256\" && o.PublicKey == nil {\n        return ErrInvalidConfig\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### MiddlewareOptions\n\n```go\n// MiddlewareOptions configures the JWT middleware behavior.\ntype MiddlewareOptions struct {\n    // Validator is the JWT validator instance\n    Validator JWTValidator\n\n    // ErrorHandler is called for validation errors (optional)\n    // If nil, default error responses are used\n    ErrorHandler func(http.ResponseWriter, error)\n\n    // ExcludePaths is a list of paths to exclude from authentication\n    ExcludePaths []string\n}\n\n// Validate checks if the middleware options are valid.\nfunc (o *MiddlewareOptions) Validate() error {\n    if o.Validator == nil {\n        return ErrInvalidConfig\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Domain Types\n\n#### JWTValidator Interface\n\n```go\n// JWTValidator validates JWT tokens and returns parsed claims.\ntype JWTValidator interface {\n    // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns the parsed claims.\n    //\n    // Returns:\n    //   - *Claims: Parsed claims on successful validation\n    //   - error: ErrInvalidTokenFormat, ErrInvalidSignature, ErrTokenExpired,\n    //            ErrInvalidIssuer, or ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm\n    ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n}\n\n// validator implements JWTValidator.\ntype validator struct {\n    opts ValidationOptions\n}\n\n// NewValidator creates a new JWTValidator with the specified options.\nfunc NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error) {\n    if err := opts.Validate(); err != nil {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrInvalidConfig, err)\n    }\n    return &validator{opts: opts}, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### parsedToken (Internal)\n\n```go\n// parsedToken represents a JWT token after initial parsing.\ntype parsedToken struct {\n    // Header contains the JWT header claims\n    Header map[string]interface{}\n\n    // Claims contains the JWT payload claims\n    Claims map[string]interface{}\n\n    // Signature is the raw signature bytes\n    Signature []byte\n\n    // raw is the original token string\n    raw string\n}\n\n// Algorithm extracts the algorithm from the header.\nfunc (t *parsedToken) Algorithm() string {\n    if alg, ok := t.Header[\"alg\"].(string); ok {\n        return alg\n    }\n    return \"\"\n}\n\n// extractClaims converts map claims to Claims struct.\nfunc (t *parsedToken) extractClaims() (*Claims, error) {\n    claims := &Claims{}\n\n    // Extract subject\n    if sub, ok := t.Claims[\"sub\"].(string); ok {\n        claims.Subject = sub\n    }\n\n    // Extract issuer\n    if iss, ok := t.Claims[\"iss\"].(string); ok {\n        claims.Issuer = iss\n    }\n\n    // Extract expiration\n    if exp, ok := t.Claims[\"exp\"].(float64); ok {\n        claims.ExpiresAt = time.Unix(int64(exp), 0)\n    } else if expStr, ok := t.Claims[\"exp\"].(string); ok {\n        if expTime, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, expStr); err == nil {\n            claims.ExpiresAt = expTime\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Extract issued-at\n    if iat, ok := t.Claims[\"iat\"].(float64); ok {\n        claims.IssuedAt = time.Unix(int64(iat), 0)\n    } else if iatStr, ok := t.Claims[\"iat\"].(string); ok {\n        if iatTime, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, iatStr); err == nil {\n            claims.IssuedAt = iatTime\n        }\n    }\n\n    return claims, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Internal Types\n\n#### Config\n\n```go\n// Config contains environment-based configuration for JWT validation.\ntype Config struct {\n    // Algorithm is the signing algorithm (HS256 or RS256)\n    Algorithm string\n\n    // Secret is the HMAC secret for HS256\n    Secret string\n\n    // PublicKeyPath is the path to the RSA public key file for RS256\n    PublicKeyPath string\n\n    // Issuer is the expected issuer claim\n    Issuer string\n\n    // ClockSkew is the clock skew tolerance duration\n    ClockSkew time.Duration\n}\n\n// LoadConfig loads configuration from environment variables.\nfunc LoadConfig() (*Config, error) {\n    cfg := &Config{\n        Algorithm: getEnvOrDefault(\"PICOD_JWT_ALG\", \"RS256\"),\n        Issuer:    os.Getenv(\"PICOD_JWT_ISSUER\"),\n        ClockSkew: defaultClockSkew,\n    }\n\n    // Issuer is required\n    if cfg.Issuer == \"\" {\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: PICOD_JWT_ISSUER is required\", ErrInvalidConfig)\n    }\n\n    // Parse clock skew\n    if skew := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW\"); skew != \"\" {\n        if d, err := time.ParseDuration(skew); err == nil {\n            cfg.ClockSkew = d\n        } else {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: invalid PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW: %v\", ErrInvalidConfig, err)\n        }\n    }\n\n    // Load algorithm-specific config\n    switch cfg.Algorithm {\n    case \"HS256\":\n        cfg.Secret = os.Getenv(\"PICOD_JWT_SECRET\")\n        if cfg.Secret == \"\" {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: PICOD_JWT_SECRET is required for HS256\", ErrInvalidConfig)\n        }\n    case \"RS256\":\n        cfg.PublicKeyPath = os.Getenv(\"PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY\")\n        if cfg.PublicKeyPath == \"\" {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY is required for RS256\", ErrInvalidConfig)\n        }\n    default:\n        return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: unsupported algorithm: %s\", ErrInvalidConfig, cfg.Algorithm)\n    }\n\n    return cfg, nil\n}\n\n// ToValidationOptions converts Config to ValidationOptions.\nfunc (c *Config) ToValidationOptions() (ValidationOptions, error) {\n    opts := ValidationOptions{\n        Algorithm:      c.Algorithm,\n        ExpectedIssuer: c.Issuer,\n        ClockSkew:      c.ClockSkew,\n        AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\", \"RS256\"},\n    }\n\n    switch c.Algorithm {\n    case \"HS256\":\n        opts.Secret = []byte(c.Secret)\n    case \"RS256\":\n        key, err := loadRSAPublicKey(c.PublicKeyPath)\n        if err != nil {\n            return ValidationOptions{}, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to load RSA public key: %w\", err)\n        }\n        opts.PublicKey = key\n    }\n\n    return opts, nil\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n```go\n// Default configuration values\nconst (\n    // defaultClockSkew is the default clock skew tolerance\n    defaultClockSkew = time.Minute\n\n    // authorizationHeader is the HTTP header name for authorization\n    authorizationHeader = \"Authorization\"\n\n    // bearerPrefix is the expected prefix for bearer tokens\n    bearerPrefix = \"Bearer \"\n\n    // tokenParts is the expected number of JWT parts (header.payload.signature)\n    tokenParts = 3\n)\n\n// Error codes for HTTP responses\nconst (\n    // ErrorCodeMissingToken indicates no authorization header\n    ErrorCodeMissingToken = \"MISSING_TOKEN\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat indicates malformed JWT\n    ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat = \"INVALID_TOKEN_FORMAT\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeInvalidSignature indicates signature verification failure\n    ErrorCodeInvalidSignature = \"INVALID_SIGNATURE\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeTokenExpired indicates expired token\n    ErrorCodeTokenExpired = \"TOKEN_EXPIRED\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeInvalidIssuer indicates issuer mismatch\n    ErrorCodeInvalidIssuer = \"INVALID_ISSUER\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeUnsupportedAlgorithm indicates unsupported signing algorithm\n    ErrorCodeUnsupportedAlgorithm = \"UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM\"\n\n    // ErrorCodeInvalidConfig indicates configuration error\n    ErrorCodeInvalidConfig = \"INVALID_CONFIG\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### JWTValidator Interface\n\n```go\n// JWTValidator is the primary interface for token validation.\ntype JWTValidator interface {\n    // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns parsed claims.\n    //\n    // Parameters:\n    //   - token: The JWT string to validate (must be in header.payload.signature format)\n    //\n    // Returns:\n    //   - *Claims: Parsed claims on successful validation\n    //   - error: Validation error with specific error type\n    //\n    // Errors:\n    //   - ErrInvalidTokenFormat: Token is malformed or missing required parts\n    //   - ErrInvalidSignature: Signature verification failed\n    //   - ErrTokenExpired: Token has expired (considering clock skew)\n    //   - ErrInvalidIssuer: Issuer claim doesn't match expected value\n    //   - ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm: Token uses an algorithm not in AllowedAlgs\n    ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n}\n\n// NewValidator creates a JWTValidator with the specified options.\n//\n// Parameters:\n//   - opts: Validation options including algorithm, keys, and validation rules\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - JWTValidator: Configured validator instance\n//   - error: Configuration validation error\nfunc NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error)\n```\n\n### Middleware Functions\n\n```go\n// JWTMiddleware creates an HTTP middleware for JWT validation.\n//\n// Parameters:\n//   - opts: Middleware configuration including validator and error handler\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - func(http.Handler) http.Handler: Middleware function that wraps handlers\n//\n// Usage:\n//   handler := JWTMiddleware(opts)(myHandler)\nfunc JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n\n// GetClaims retrieves validated claims from request context.\n//\n// Parameters:\n//   - ctx: Context from an HTTP request that passed through JWTMiddleware\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - *Claims: Parsed JWT claims (nil if not found)\n//   - bool: true if claims were found in context\nfunc GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n\n// ContextWithClaims adds claims to a context.\n//\n// Parameters:\n//   - ctx: Base context\n//   - claims: JWT claims to add\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - context.Context: Context with claims attached\nfunc ContextWithClaims(ctx context.Context, claims *Claims) context.Context\n```\n\n### Configuration Functions\n\n```go\n// LoadConfig loads JWT configuration from environment variables.\n//\n// Required environment variables:\n//   - PICOD_JWT_ISSUER: Expected issuer claim\n//\n// Required for HS256:\n//   - PICOD_JWT_SECRET: HMAC secret\n//\n// Required for RS256:\n//   - PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY: Path to RSA public key PEM file\n//\n// Optional:\n//   - PICOD_JWT_ALG: Algorithm (default: \"RS256\")\n//   - PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW: Clock skew tolerance (default: \"1m\")\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - *Config: Loaded configuration\n//   - error: Configuration loading error\nfunc LoadConfig() (*Config, error)\n\n// LoadValidatorFromEnv creates a JWTValidator from environment configuration.\n//\n// This is a convenience function that loads config and creates a validator.\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - JWTValidator: Configured validator\n//   - error: Configuration or initialization error\nfunc LoadValidatorFromEnv() (JWTValidator, error)\n```\n\n### Helper Functions\n\n```go\n// ExtractBearerToken extracts the bearer token from an Authorization header.\n//\n// Parameters:\n//   - header: The Authorization header value\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - string: Extracted token\n//   - error: ErrMissingToken or ErrInvalidTokenFormat\nfunc ExtractBearerToken(header string) (string, error)\n\n// IsExcludedPath checks if a request path should be excluded from auth.\n//\n// Parameters:\n//   - path: Request path\n//   - exclusions: List of excluded path patterns\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - bool: true if path should be excluded\nfunc IsExcludedPath(path string, exclusions []string) bool\n\n// WriteErrorResponse writes a standardized JSON error response.\n//\n// Parameters:\n//   - w: Response writer\n//   - status: HTTP status code\n//   - code: Error code\n//   - message: Human-readable error message\nfunc WriteErrorResponse(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, code, message string)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories and Codes\n\n| Error | Code | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n|-------|------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ErrMissingToken` | `MISSING_TOKEN` | No Authorization header present | No | Return HTTP 401 |\n| `ErrInvalidTokenFormat` | `INVALID_TOKEN_FORMAT` | Malformed JWT structure | No | Return HTTP 401 |\n| `ErrInvalidSignature` | `INVALID_SIGNATURE` | Signature verification failed | No | Return HTTP 401 |\n| `ErrTokenExpired` | `TOKEN_EXPIRED` | Token has expired | No | Return HTTP 401 |\n| `ErrInvalidIssuer` | `INVALID_ISSUER` | Issuer claim mismatch | No | Return HTTP 403 |\n| `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm` | `UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM` | Algorithm not in allowed list | No | Return HTTP 401 |\n| `ErrInvalidConfig` | `INVALID_CONFIG` | Configuration error | No | Fail on startup |\n\n### Sentinel Errors\n\n```go\n// JWT validation errors\nvar (\n    ErrMissingToken         = errors.New(\"jwt: missing bearer token\")\n    ErrInvalidTokenFormat   = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid token format\")\n    ErrInvalidSignature     = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid signature\")\n    ErrTokenExpired         = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n    ErrInvalidIssuer        = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid issuer\")\n    ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm = errors.New(\"jwt: unsupported algorithm\")\n    ErrInvalidConfig        = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid configuration\")\n)\n```\n\n### ValidationError Structure\n\n```go\n// ValidationError represents a JWT validation error with context.\ntype ValidationError struct {\n    // Code is the machine-readable error code\n    Code string `json:\"code\"`\n\n    // Message is the human-readable error message\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n\n    // Details contains additional error context\n    Details map[string]interface{} `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n\n    // underlying is the wrapped error\n    underlying error\n}\n\n// Error returns the error string.\nfunc (e *ValidationError) Error() string {\n    if e.underlying != nil {\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (%v)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.underlying)\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", e.Code, e.Message)\n}\n\n// Unwrap returns the wrapped error.\nfunc (e *ValidationError) Unwrap() error {\n    return e.underlying\n}\n\n// NewValidationError creates a new ValidationError.\nfunc NewValidationError(code, message string, underlying error) *ValidationError {\n    return &ValidationError{\n        Code:       code,\n        Message:    message,\n        underlying: underlying,\n    }\n}\n\n// WithDetails adds details to the error.\nfunc (e *ValidationError) WithDetails(details map[string]interface{}) *ValidationError {\n    e.Details = details\n    return e\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n#### Token Validation Error Handling\n\n```go\nfunc (v *validator) ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error) {\n    // Parse the token\n    parsed, err := parseToken(token)\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, NewValidationError(\n            ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat,\n            \"failed to parse token\",\n            ErrInvalidTokenFormat,\n        )\n    }\n\n    // Validate algorithm\n    alg := parsed.Algorithm()\n    if !v.isAllowedAlgorithm(alg) {\n        return nil, NewValidationError(\n            ErrorCodeUnsupportedAlgorithm,\n            fmt.Sprintf(\"algorithm %s is not allowed\", alg),\n            ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm,\n        ).WithDetails(map[string]interface{}{\"algorithm\": alg})\n    }\n\n    if alg != v.opts.Algorithm {\n        return nil, NewValidationError(\n            ErrorCodeUnsupportedAlgorithm,\n            fmt.Sprintf(\"expected algorithm %s, got %s\", v.opts.Algorithm, alg),\n            ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm,\n        )\n    }\n\n    // Verify signature\n    if err := v.verifySignature(parsed); err != nil {\n        return nil, NewValidationError(\n            ErrorCodeInvalidSignature,\n            \"signature verification failed\",\n            ErrInvalidSignature,\n        )\n    }\n\n    // Extract and validate claims\n    claims, err := parsed.extractClaims()\n    if err != nil {\n        return nil, NewValidationError(\n            ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat,\n            \"failed to extract claims\",\n            err,\n        )\n    }\n\n    // Check expiration\n    if claims.IsExpired(v.opts.ClockSkew) {\n        return nil, NewValidationError(\n            ErrorCodeTokenExpired,\n            \"token has expired\",\n            ErrTokenExpired,\n        ).WithDetails(map[string]interface{}{\n            \"expired_at\": claims.ExpiresAt,\n            \"now\":        time.Now(),\n        })\n    }\n\n    // Validate issuer\n    if !claims.IsValidIssuer(v.opts.ExpectedIssuer) {\n        return nil, NewValidationError(\n            ErrorCodeInvalidIssuer,\n            fmt.Sprintf(\"expected issuer %s, got %s\", v.opts.ExpectedIssuer, claims.Issuer),\n            ErrInvalidIssuer,\n        ).WithDetails(map[string]interface{}{\n            \"expected\": v.opts.ExpectedIssuer,\n            \"actual\":   claims.Issuer,\n        })\n    }\n\n    return claims, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Middleware Error Handling\n\n```go\nfunc JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler {\n    return func(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n        return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n            // Check excluded paths\n            if IsExcludedPath(r.URL.Path, opts.ExcludePaths) {\n                next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n                return\n            }\n\n            // Extract token\n            authHeader := r.Header.Get(authorizationHeader)\n            if authHeader == \"\" {\n                handleAuthError(w, opts.ErrorHandler, ErrMissingToken)\n                return\n            }\n\n            token, err := ExtractBearerToken(authHeader)\n            if err != nil {\n                handleAuthError(w, opts.ErrorHandler, err)\n                return\n            }\n\n            // Validate token\n            claims, err := opts.Validator.ValidateToken(token)\n            if err != nil {\n                handleAuthError(w, opts.ErrorHandler, err)\n                return\n            }\n\n            // Add claims to context and call next handler\n            ctx := ContextWithClaims(r.Context(), claims)\n            next.ServeHTTP(w, r.WithContext(ctx))\n        })\n    }\n}\n\nfunc handleAuthError(w http.ResponseWriter, handler func(http.ResponseWriter, error), err error) {\n    if handler != nil {\n        handler(w, err)\n        return\n    }\n\n    // Default error handling\n    var status int\n    var code, message string\n\n    switch {\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrMissingToken):\n        status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n        code = ErrorCodeMissingToken\n        message = \"missing bearer token\"\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrInvalidTokenFormat):\n        status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n        code = ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat\n        message = \"invalid token format\"\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrInvalidSignature):\n        status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n        code = ErrorCodeInvalidSignature\n        message = \"invalid token signature\"\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrTokenExpired):\n        status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n        code = ErrorCodeTokenExpired\n        message = \"token expired\"\n    case errors.Is(err, ErrInvalidIssuer):\n        status = http.StatusForbidden\n        code = ErrorCodeInvalidIssuer\n        message = \"invalid issuer\"\n    default:\n        status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n        code = ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat\n        message = \"authentication failed\"\n    }\n\n    WriteErrorResponse(w, status, code, message)\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### validator_test.go\n\n```go\nfunc TestValidator_ValidateToken_HS256_Success(t *testing.T) {\n    // Create validator with HMAC secret\n    opts := ValidationOptions{\n        Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n        Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n        ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n        ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n        AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"},\n    }\n\n    validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Generate valid token\n    token := generateTestTokenHS256(\"HS256\", \"test-issuer\", time.Hour)\n\n    // Validate\n    claims, err := validator.ValidateToken(token)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"test-user\", claims.Subject)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"test-issuer\", claims.Issuer)\n}\n\nfunc TestValidator_ValidateToken_RS256_Success(t *testing.T) {\n    // Load test RSA key\n    privateKey, publicKey := generateTestRSAKeys()\n\n    opts := ValidationOptions{\n        Algorithm:      \"RS256\",\n        PublicKey:      publicKey,\n        ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n        ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n        AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"RS256\"},\n    }\n\n    validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Generate valid token\n    token := generateTestTokenRS256(privateKey, \"test-issuer\", time.Hour)\n\n    // Validate\n    claims, err := validator.ValidateToken(token)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"test-user\", claims.Subject)\n}\n\nfunc TestValidator_ValidateToken_InvalidSignature(t *testing.T) {\n    opts := ValidationOptions{\n        Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n        Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n        ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n        ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n        AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"},\n    }\n\n    validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Generate token with wrong secret\n    token := generateTestTokenHS256(\"HS256\", \"test-issuer\", time.Hour, \"wrong-secret\")\n\n    // Validate\n    _, err = validator.ValidateToken(token)\n    assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrInvalidSignature)\n}\n\nfunc TestValidator_ValidateToken_Expired(t *testing.T) {\n    opts := ValidationOptions{\n        Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n        Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n        ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n        ClockSkew:      0, // No skew\n        AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"},\n    }\n\n    validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Generate expired token\n    token := generateTestTokenHS256(\"HS256\", \"test-issuer\", -time.Hour)\n\n    // Validate\n    _, err = validator.ValidateToken(token)\n    assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrTokenExpired)\n}\n\nfunc TestValidator_ValidateToken_ClockSkew(t *testing.T) {\n    opts := ValidationOptions{\n        Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n        Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n        ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n        ClockSkew:      time.Minute * 5, // 5 minute skew\n        AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"},\n    }\n\n    validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Generate token expired 30 seconds ago\n    token := generateTestTokenHS256(\"HS256\", \"test-issuer\", -time.Second*30)\n\n    // Should pass with clock skew\n    claims, err := validator.ValidateToken(token)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.NotNil(t, claims)\n}\n\nfunc TestValidator_ValidateToken_WrongIssuer(t *testing.T) {\n    opts := ValidationOptions{\n        Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n        Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n        ExpectedIssuer: \"expected-issuer\",\n        ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n        AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"},\n    }\n\n    validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Generate token with wrong issuer\n    token := generateTestTokenHS256(\"HS256\", \"wrong-issuer\", time.Hour)\n\n    // Validate\n    _, err = validator.ValidateToken(token)\n    assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrInvalidIssuer)\n}\n\nfunc TestValidator_ValidateToken_UnsupportedAlgorithm(t *testing.T) {\n    opts := ValidationOptions{\n        Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n        Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n        ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n        ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n        AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"}, // Only HS256 allowed\n    }\n\n    validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Generate RS256 token\n    _, publicKey := generateTestRSAKeys()\n    token := generateTestTokenRS256(nil, \"test-issuer\", time.Hour)\n\n    // Validate - should fail on algorithm mismatch\n    _, err = validator.ValidateToken(token)\n    assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm)\n}\n```\n\n#### middleware_test.go\n\n```go\nfunc TestMiddleware_ValidToken(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup\n    mockValidator := &mockJWTValidator{\n        validateFunc: func(token string) (*Claims, error) {\n            return &Claims{\n                Subject:   \"test-user\",\n                Issuer:    \"test-issuer\",\n                ExpiresAt: time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n            }, nil\n        },\n    }\n\n    opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n        Validator: mockValidator,\n    }\n\n    // Create test handler that checks for claims\n    var capturedClaims *Claims\n    handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        claims, ok := GetClaims(r.Context())\n        if ok {\n            capturedClaims = claims\n        }\n        w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    })\n\n    // Wrap with middleware\n    wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n\n    // Create request with valid token\n    req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n    req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer valid-token\")\n\n    // Execute\n    rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n\n    // Assert\n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, rr.Code)\n    assert.NotNil(t, capturedClaims)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"test-user\", capturedClaims.Subject)\n}\n\nfunc TestMiddleware_MissingToken(t *testing.T) {\n    opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n        Validator: &mockJWTValidator{},\n    }\n\n    handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    })\n\n    wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n\n    // Request without Authorization header\n    req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n    rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n\n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusUnauthorized, rr.Code)\n    assert.Contains(t, rr.Body.String(), \"missing bearer token\")\n}\n\nfunc TestMiddleware_InvalidFormat(t *testing.T) {\n    opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n        Validator: &mockJWTValidator{},\n    }\n\n    handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    })\n\n    wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n\n    // Request with malformed header\n    req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n    req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"InvalidFormat\")\n    rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n\n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusUnauthorized, rr.Code)\n    assert.Contains(t, rr.Body.String(), \"invalid token format\")\n}\n\nfunc TestMiddleware_ExpiredToken(t *testing.T) {\n    mockValidator := &mockJWTValidator{\n        validateFunc: func(token string) (*Claims, error) {\n            return nil, ErrTokenExpired\n        },\n    }\n\n    opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n        Validator: mockValidator,\n    }\n\n    handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    })\n\n    wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n\n    req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n    req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer expired-token\")\n    rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n\n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusUnauthorized, rr.Code)\n    assert.Contains(t, rr.Body.String(), \"token expired\")\n}\n\nfunc TestMiddleware_InvalidIssuer(t *testing.T) {\n    mockValidator := &mockJWTValidator{\n        validateFunc: func(token string) (*Claims, error) {\n            return nil, ErrInvalidIssuer\n        },\n    }\n\n    opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n        Validator: mockValidator,\n    }\n\n    handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    })\n\n    wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n\n    req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n    req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer wrong-issuer-token\")\n    rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n\n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusForbidden, rr.Code)\n    assert.Contains(t, rr.Body.String(), \"invalid issuer\")\n}\n\nfunc TestMiddleware_ExcludedPath(t *testing.T) {\n    opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n        Validator:    &mockJWTValidator{},\n        ExcludePaths: []string{\"/health\", \"/metrics\"},\n    }\n\n    handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    })\n\n    wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n\n    // Request to excluded path without token\n    req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/health\", nil)\n    rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n\n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, rr.Code)\n}\n\nfunc TestMiddleware_ContextPropagation(t *testing.T) {\n    expectedClaims := &Claims{\n        Subject:   \"test-user\",\n        Issuer:    \"test-issuer\",\n        ExpiresAt: time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n    }\n\n    mockValidator := &mockJWTValidator{\n        validateFunc: func(token string) (*Claims, error) {\n            return expectedClaims, nil\n        },\n    }\n\n    opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n        Validator: mockValidator,\n    }\n\n    claimsReceived := false\n    handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        claims, ok := GetClaims(r.Context())\n        if ok && claims.Subject == expectedClaims.Subject {\n            claimsReceived = true\n        }\n        w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    })\n\n    wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n\n    req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n    req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer valid-token\")\n    rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n\n    assert.True(t, claimsReceived)\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestIntegration_EndToEnd(t *testing.T) {\n    if testing.Short() {\n        t.Skip(\"Skipping integration test\")\n    }\n\n    // Generate real RSA key pair\n    privateKey, publicKey := generateTestRSAKeys()\n\n    // Create validator\n    opts := ValidationOptions{\n        Algorithm:      \"RS256\",\n        PublicKey:      publicKey,\n        ExpectedIssuer: \"integration-test\",\n        ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n        AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"RS256\"},\n    }\n\n    validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n\n    // Create middleware\n    middlewareOpts := MiddlewareOptions{\n        Validator: validator,\n    }\n\n    // Create handler\n    handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n        claims, ok := GetClaims(r.Context())\n        if !ok {\n            w.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n            return\n        }\n        w.Header().Set(\"X-User\", claims.Subject)\n        w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n    })\n\n    wrapped := JWTMiddleware(middlewareOpts)(handler)\n\n    // Generate real token\n    token := generateRealJWT(privateKey, \"RS256\", \"integration-test\", \"test-user\", time.Hour)\n\n    // Make request\n    req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/api/resource\", nil)\n    req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+token)\n    rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n    wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n\n    // Verify\n    assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, rr.Code)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"test-user\", rr.Header().Get(\"X-User\"))\n}\n\nfunc TestIntegration_Configuration(t *testing.T) {\n    // Set environment variables\n    t.Setenv(\"PICOD_JWT_ISSUER\", \"test-issuer\")\n    t.Setenv(\"PICOD_JWT_SECRET\", \"test-secret\")\n    t.Setenv(\"PICOD_JWT_ALG\", \"HS256\")\n    t.Setenv(\"PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW\", \"2m\")\n\n    // Load configuration\n    cfg, err := LoadConfig()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"HS256\", cfg.Algorithm)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"test-issuer\", cfg.Issuer)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"test-secret\", cfg.Secret)\n    assert.Equal(t, 2*time.Minute, cfg.ClockSkew)\n\n    // Convert to options\n    opts, err := cfg.ToValidationOptions()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"HS256\", opts.Algorithm)\n    assert.Equal(t, []byte(\"test-secret\"), opts.Secret)\n}\n```\n\n### Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Run all JWT middleware tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n\n# Run specific test categories\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -run \"TestValidateToken\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -run \"TestMiddleware\"\n\n# With coverage\ngo test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out\n```\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Token Transmission\n- Tokens MUST be transmitted via HTTPS in production\n- HTTP is only allowed in development with appropriate warnings\n- Authorization header is the only supported token transport\n\n### Key Management\n- HMAC secrets MUST be securely stored (e.g., Kubernetes secrets)\n- RSA public keys should be rotated periodically\n- Private keys for token signing are NOT handled by this middleware\n- Keys should have sufficient length (HMAC: 256+ bits, RSA: 2048+ bits)\n\n### Validation Security\n- Short token expiration recommended (minutes to hours)\n- Clock skew tolerance kept minimal (default 1 minute)\n- Algorithm explicitly specified to prevent \"none\" algorithm attacks\n- Allowed algorithms whitelist prevents unexpected algorithm usage\n- Path traversal in excluded paths must be handled carefully\n\n### Implementation Security\n- Constant-time comparison for HMAC verification\n- No sensitive data in error messages\n- Context propagation follows request lifecycle\n- No token logging (only metadata)\n\n---\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Algorithm Performance\n| Algorithm | Relative Speed | Use Case |\n|-----------|----------------|----------|\n| HS256 | Fast (1x) | Internal services, symmetric trust |\n| RS256 | Slower (~10x) | External clients, asymmetric trust |\n\n### Optimization Strategies\n- RSA signature verification is slower than HMAC\n- Consider caching parsed keys (done at initialization)\n- Minimize allocations in hot path (token validation)\n- Early rejection for missing headers (before validation)\n- Excluded paths bypass validation entirely\n\n### Resource Usage\n- Memory: Minimal (only stores key material and config)\n- CPU: Depends on algorithm (HS256 < RS256)\n- Network: None (validation is local)\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n### With PicoD Command Execution (AR-015)\n\n```go\n// Example: Applying JWT middleware to PicoD API routes\nfunc SetupPicoDRoutes(mux *http.ServeMux, validator JWTValidator) {\n    opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n        Validator:    validator,\n        ExcludePaths: []string{\"/health\", \"/ready\"},\n    }\n\n    // Apply middleware to protected routes\n    mux.Handle(\"/api/v1/exec\", JWTMiddleware(opts)(execHandler))\n    mux.Handle(\"/api/v1/status\", JWTMiddleware(opts)(statusHandler))\n    mux.Handle(\"/api/v1/logs\", JWTMiddleware(opts)(logsHandler))\n\n    // Public routes (no middleware)\n    mux.Handle(\"/health\", healthHandler)\n    mux.Handle(\"/ready\", readyHandler)\n}\n```\n\n### With Existing Router JWT\n\nThe PicoD JWT middleware uses consistent patterns with `pkg/router/jwt_*.go`:\n- Similar Claims structure\n- Compatible error handling\n- Consistent context key usage\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"crypto/rsa\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"net/http\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"strings\"\n    \"time\"\n\n    \"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n)\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose | Version |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT parsing and validation | v5.2.1 |\n| Standard library | Crypto, HTTP, context | Go 1.23+ |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [PicoD JWT Design](changes/AR-017/design.md) — Short design document\n- [PicoD JWT Delta Spec](changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md) — API specification\n- [PicoD JWT Tests](changes/AR-017/tests.md) — Test specifications\n- [PicoD JWT Plan](changes/AR-017/plan.md) — Implementation plan\n- [AR-015 Command Execution](changes/AR-015/design.md) — Base API protected by this middleware\n- [RFC 7519](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519) — JSON Web Token (JWT)\n- [RFC 7515](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7515) — JSON Web Signature (JWS)\n\n---\n\n*AR-017 — Module: pkg/picod/jwt — Language: Go — Size: S*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/spec.yaml":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt_types.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":130,"character":25},"end":{"line":130,"character":36}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":243,"character":33},"end":{"line":243,"character":44}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"},{"range":{"start":{"line":246,"character":37},"end":{"line":246,"character":48}},"severity":4,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/go/analysis/passes/modernize#any"},"source":"any","message":"interface{} can be replaced by any"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/router/jwt.go":[{"range":{"start":{"line":41,"character":1},"end":{"line":41,"character":11}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"const \"rsaKeySize\" is unused","tags":[1]},{"range":{"start":{"line":42,"character":1},"end":{"line":42,"character":14}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"const \"jwtExpiration\" is unused","tags":[1]},{"range":{"start":{"line":43,"character":1},"end":{"line":43,"character":18}},"severity":3,"code":"default","codeDescription":{"href":"https://pkg.go.dev/golang.org/x/tools/gopls/internal/analysis/unusedfunc"},"source":"unusedfunc","message":"const \"refreshExpiration\" is unused","tags":[1]}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":18,"character":42},"end":{"line":18,"character":53}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 should be direct"},{"range":{"start":{"line":35,"character":31},"end":{"line":35,"character":42}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/google/uuid should be direct"}]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775878249829,"end":1775878250595}}}}
