{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775878265016,"sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","part":{"id":"prt_d7a97d3a5001SHoBDEOG32eBIJ","messageID":"msg_d7a97a0980018Fm4ayf52I4NL8","sessionID":"ses_2856da7a7ffejiH1godPicAamU","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:13","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","limit":50},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 Design: PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-017  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S (Small)\n9: \n10: The PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms, validates standard claims (expiration, issuer), and integrates with the HTTP middleware chain to protect PicoD command execution endpoints (AR-015).\n11: \n12: This implementation integrates with:\n13: - **PicoD Command Execution (AR-015)**: Provides authentication layer for command execution endpoints\n14: - **Router JWT (existing)**: Uses consistent JWT patterns with the router package\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## Architecture\n19: \n20: ### High-Level Design\n21: \n22: ```\n23: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n24: │                         Client Application                                   │\n25: │                    (with JWT from Identity Provider)                         │\n26: └─────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────┘\n27:                                   │\n28:                                   ▼\n29: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n30: │                         HTTP Server Layer                                    │\n31: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n32: │  │                     JWTMiddleware                                       │  │\n33: │  │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌───────────┐  │  │\n34: │  │  │   Extract   │──►│   Parse     │──►│   Verify    │──►│ Validate  │  │  │\n35: │  │  │    Token    │   │   Header    │   │  Signature  │   │  Claims   │  │  │\n36: │  │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────┬─────┘  │  │\n37: │  │                                                              │        │  │\n38: │  │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘        │  │\n39: │  │  │                                                                   │  │\n40: │  │  ▼                                                                   │  │\n41: │  │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐                │  │\n42: │  │  │    Inject   │──►│    Call     │──►│   Handler   │                │  │\n43: │  │  │   Claims    │   │   Handler   │   │  Response   │                │  │\n44: │  │  │  to Context │   │             │   │             │                │  │\n45: │  │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘                │  │\n46: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n47: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n48: │                      JWT Validation Layer                                    │\n49: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │\n50: │  │  Token Parser    │  │  Signature Verif │  │  Claims Validator        │   │\n\n(Showing lines 1-50 of 1397. Use offset=51 to continue.)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 Design: PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S (Small)\n\nThe PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms, validates standard claims (expiration, issuer), and integrates with the HTTP middleware chain to protect PicoD command execution endpoints (AR-015).\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **PicoD Command Execution (AR-015)**: Provides authentication layer for command execution endpoints\n- **Router JWT (existing)**: Uses consistent JWT patterns with the router package\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design","truncated":true,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775878265003,"end":1775878265013}}}}
